WEBVTT

00:02.793 --> 00:05.426
Meredith:
CANCER IS A BIOLOGICAL BULLY,

00:05.426 --> 00:07.508
ALWAYS PICKING A FIGHT,

00:07.508 --> 00:09.390
AND IT'LL SNEAK UP ON YOU.

00:09.390 --> 00:11.932
CAN WE JUST STAY IN BED
ALL DAY?

00:11.932 --> 00:13.264
I COULD BE INTO THAT.

00:13.264 --> 00:14.265
[ LAUGHS ]

00:14.265 --> 00:17.268
YOU ARE NOT MAKING THIS
ANY EASIER.

00:17.268 --> 00:18.269
[ MOANS ]

00:18.269 --> 00:19.440
OKAY, OKAY, 15 MINUTES.

00:19.440 --> 00:20.691
I HAVE 15 MINUTES

00:20.691 --> 00:23.314
UNTIL I ABSOLUTELY
HAVE TO GET UP AND GET GOING.

00:23.314 --> 00:24.235
ALL RIGHT, WELL,

00:24.235 --> 00:26.237
THEN LET'S MAKE THE MOST
OF THE NEXT 15 MINUTES!

00:26.237 --> 00:28.149
IT'LL WAIT
UNTIL THE BODY FEELS SAFE,

00:28.149 --> 00:30.451
UNTIL IT FEELS
HEALTHY AND STRONG...

00:30.451 --> 00:33.204
Emma: I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M DATING
A MAN WHO LIVES IN A TIN CAN.

00:33.204 --> 00:35.656
[ OWEN CHUCKLES ]
A TIN CAN ON WHEELS.

00:35.656 --> 00:37.748
[ Laughing ]
YOU EVER THINK OF MOVING

00:37.748 --> 00:39.540
TO A PLACE
THAT CAN'T ROLL AWAY?

00:39.540 --> 00:41.462
I...HAVEN'T GIVEN IT
MUCH THOUGHT.

00:41.462 --> 00:42.463
MMM.

00:42.463 --> 00:44.375
NOT THAT I DON'T LOVE
THE TRAILER

00:44.375 --> 00:46.127
AND THE ROUGHING IT
IN NATURE.

00:46.127 --> 00:47.128
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

00:47.128 --> 00:48.299
IT'S LIKE CAMPING.

00:48.299 --> 00:51.262
MMM. WAIT. WAIT.
YOU HATE CAMPING.

00:51.262 --> 00:52.763
I HATE CAMPING. I DO.
YEAH.

00:52.763 --> 00:54.765
YEAH.
[ LAUGHS ]

00:57.348 --> 01:00.271
WELL, MAYBE WE SHOULD
LOOK AT GETTING

01:00.271 --> 01:02.603
A BIGGER PLACE...
TOGETHER.

01:02.603 --> 01:06.357
I THOUGHT YOU HADN'T
GIVEN IT MUCH THOUGHT.

01:06.357 --> 01:09.110
I JUST DID.
I'M A FAST THINKER.

01:09.110 --> 01:10.401
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
[ SMOOCHES ]

01:10.401 --> 01:12.493
I THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

01:12.493 --> 01:14.245
I'M A FAST THINKER, TOO.

01:14.245 --> 01:16.827
[ LAUGHS ]

01:16.827 --> 01:19.500
THAT'S WHEN CANCER
WILL MOVE ON IN

01:19.500 --> 01:21.332
AND GET BIGGER AND BIGGER.

01:21.332 --> 01:24.465
WHAT DO YOU THINK --
THE BLUE OR THE, UH, BURGUNDY?

01:24.465 --> 01:26.507
THE BLUE MAKES YOU LOOK
TOO HANDSOME.
OH.

01:26.507 --> 01:28.419
YOU DON'T WANT THE PRESIDENT
TO BE DISTRACTED

01:28.419 --> 01:29.800
BY THOSE
PIERCING BLUE EYES.

01:29.800 --> 01:31.302
OH, YOU WANT ME
TO GET THE JOB.

01:31.302 --> 01:33.344
I WANT NEUROSURGEON DR. SHEPHERD
TO GET THE JOB.

01:33.344 --> 01:35.426
I DON'T WANT MY HUSBAND
DR. SHEPHERD TO GET THE JOB.

01:35.426 --> 01:37.428
THAT'S COMPLICATED.

01:37.428 --> 01:39.480
YES, WELL,
I'M COMPLICATED.

01:39.480 --> 01:41.182
I'M GONNA TAKE A SHOWER NOW.

01:41.182 --> 01:42.273
SO AM I.

01:42.273 --> 01:43.984
NO.
IT'S BEEN THREE WEEKS.

01:43.984 --> 01:45.526
YOU WENT BACK
ON YOUR PROMISE.

01:45.526 --> 01:48.149
I CAN'T SLEEP WITH A MAN
WHO'S A LYING LIAR.

01:48.149 --> 01:49.900
WHAT IF I PUT ON
THE BLUE TIE?

01:49.900 --> 01:51.942
NOPE.

01:51.942 --> 01:54.695
YOU'RE HAVING FUN.
YOU DELIGHT IN MY PAIN.

01:54.695 --> 01:56.737
[ WATER RUNNING ]
I JUST TOOK OFF MY ROBE.

01:56.737 --> 01:59.410
NOW I'M SOAPING MYSELF UP.
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:59.410 --> 02:01.412
OH, MY GOODNESS.

02:01.412 --> 02:03.454
THE BODY
NEVER EVEN SEES IT COMING...

02:03.454 --> 02:04.505
CALLIE, COME ON.
WE GOT TO GO.

02:04.505 --> 02:06.337
WELL, WE SAID
WE'D EACH DO A BOX A DAY.

02:06.337 --> 02:08.128
I'M DOING MINE,
SO COME DO YOURS.

02:08.128 --> 02:09.800
NO, NO, NO.
SOPHIA'S READY TO GO.

02:09.800 --> 02:11.342
COME ON --
IT'LL JUST TAKE A MINUTE.

02:11.342 --> 02:12.513
CALLIE --
UNPACK THIS BOX!

02:12.513 --> 02:13.884
[ SCOFFS ]

02:14.925 --> 02:18.179
YOU KNOW, THE WHOLE WORLD
IS NOT GOING TO END

02:18.179 --> 02:19.890
IF I DON'T OPEN THIS BOX --

02:21.392 --> 02:22.643
OPEN IT.

02:25.396 --> 02:29.440
...BECAUSE CANCER IS THE MASTER
OF SURPRISES.

02:29.440 --> 02:30.571
I INSCRIBED THE BAND

02:30.571 --> 02:32.733
WITH THE DATE WE MOVED
INTO THIS HOUSE.

02:32.733 --> 02:35.366
OUR NEW START.

02:41.081 --> 02:43.454
CALLIOPE IPHEGENIA TORRES --

02:43.454 --> 02:44.915
PUT IT ON!

02:46.457 --> 02:47.878
April: TAKE IT OFF!

02:47.878 --> 02:49.550
TAKE IT OFF!
YOUR RING.
Jackson: OH.

02:49.550 --> 02:50.421
TAKE OFF YOUR RING.

02:50.421 --> 02:53.254
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

02:53.254 --> 02:54.295
THANK YOU, DR. AVERY.

02:54.295 --> 02:55.756
I AM, UM --
I'M GLAD YOU AGREE

02:55.756 --> 02:58.469
THAT A MICROVASCULAR FREE FLAP
IS CALLED FOR IN THIS...

02:58.469 --> 03:00.471
MM-HMM. MM-HMM. YEAH.
...PARTICULAR SC-- SCENARIO.

03:00.471 --> 03:02.393
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

03:02.393 --> 03:04.435
WELL, YOU ARE NOT GETTING
YOUR SECURITY DEPOSIT BACK.

03:04.435 --> 03:05.726
GLAD I NEVER
GAVE YOU ONE.

03:05.726 --> 03:07.147
YOU GUYS
ARE REALLY SERIOUS.

03:07.147 --> 03:08.148
YES, WE ARE.

03:09.610 --> 03:10.731
WHAT DID I MISS?

03:10.731 --> 03:13.193
OWEN AND EMMA
ARE MOVING IN TOGETHER.

03:13.193 --> 03:14.525
HE HOLDS A MEETING
FOR THAT?

03:14.525 --> 03:15.866
[ ELEVATOR DINGS ]

03:15.866 --> 03:17.027
THANK YOU ALL FOR COMING.

03:17.027 --> 03:18.118
I KNOW YOU'RE ALL BUSY,
SO THIS WON'T TAKE LONG.

03:18.118 --> 03:19.370
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

03:19.370 --> 03:23.954
THE BOARD HAS JUST APPROVED
A NEW NON-FRATERNIZATION POLICY.

03:23.954 --> 03:26.627
THIS HOSPITAL HAS TO BE
A SAFE WORK ENVIRONMENT

03:26.627 --> 03:29.039
WHERE OUR FOCUS REMAINS CLEARLY
ON PROVIDING

03:29.039 --> 03:31.131
THE BEST PATIENT CARE POSSIBLE.

03:31.131 --> 03:32.333
MOVING FORWARD,

03:32.333 --> 03:34.094
ALL RELATIONSHIPS
WITH CO-WORKERS

03:34.094 --> 03:35.596
WILL BE DISCOURAGED.

03:35.596 --> 03:38.429
AND ALL RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN
SUPERIORS AND SUBORDINATES

03:38.429 --> 03:40.220
IS STRICTLY PROHIBITED.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.763
YOU WILL ALL RECEIVE
A COPY OF THE NEW RULES.

03:42.763 --> 03:45.516
YOUR SUPERVISORS WILL ARRANGE
MEETINGS TO GO OVER THE DETAILS.

03:45.516 --> 03:47.558
AND THAT'S IT.
LET'S GET BACK TO WORK.

03:47.558 --> 03:49.149
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

03:49.149 --> 03:50.651
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

03:50.651 --> 03:54.405
SO, UM,
YOU'RE THE PANTY POLICE NOW?

03:54.405 --> 03:55.486
[ SCOFFS ]

03:55.486 --> 03:57.568
I KNOW
THERE WILL BE SOME FEELINGS,

03:57.568 --> 03:58.779
AND I KNOW
YOU'VE ESTABLISHED

03:58.779 --> 04:00.451
GOOD RELATIONSHIPS
WITH THE RESIDENTS,

04:00.451 --> 04:01.622
SO I'D LIKE YOU
TO TAKE THEM TODAY

04:01.622 --> 04:03.784
AND MAKE SURE THAT
THEY UNDERSTAND THE POLICY.

04:03.784 --> 04:06.166
SO YOU WANT ME
TO BE THE PANTY POLICE.

04:06.166 --> 04:08.038
ALL DUE RESPECT,
NUTS TO THAT.

04:08.038 --> 04:10.791
DR. HUNT, WE HAVE SOME QUESTIONS
ABOUT THE POLICY.

04:10.791 --> 04:14.545
DR. WEBBER CAN ANSWER
ALL OF YOUR QUESTIONS.

04:14.545 --> 04:16.216
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

04:16.216 --> 04:17.468
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

04:19.510 --> 04:21.642
Woman over P.A. system:
RADIOLOGY.

04:21.642 --> 04:24.144
RADIOLOGY.

04:24.144 --> 04:25.686
HEY, RORY.
HOW YOU DOING?

04:25.686 --> 04:28.188
BESIDES THE FACT THAT I HAVE
BONE CANCER, I'M GREAT.

04:28.188 --> 04:30.441
SERIOUSLY.
LOOK AT THIS POLISH.

04:30.441 --> 04:31.772
IT'S CALLED
"BAD TO THE BONE."

04:31.772 --> 04:32.603
MM!

04:32.603 --> 04:33.734
WE SAW IT AT THE DRUGSTORE,

04:33.734 --> 04:35.566
AND IT WAS LIKE
GOD ORDERED US TO BUY IT.

04:35.566 --> 04:37.528
HEY, I DON'T TAKE
ANY ORDERS FROM ANY GOD

04:37.528 --> 04:38.899
WHO GIVES ME CANCER TWICE.

04:38.899 --> 04:41.071
DUDE, YOUR STUPID BRAIN CANCER
GOT US A PUPPY,

04:41.071 --> 04:42.323
AND YOUR STUPID BONE CANCER

04:42.323 --> 04:43.864
IS GETTING US BOTH
OUT OF FINALS.

04:43.864 --> 04:44.905
YOU'RE RIGHT.

04:44.905 --> 04:46.707
YAY, GOD.
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:46.707 --> 04:48.208
TAKE
A DEEP BREATH.

04:48.208 --> 04:49.500
Callie: ALL RIGHT, SO, TODAY'S
GONNA BE A PIECE OF CAKE.

04:49.500 --> 04:51.332
WE'RE GONNA STAGE THE TUMOR,
DO A BIOPSY,

04:51.332 --> 04:53.043
AND THEN WE'LL COME UP
WITH A TREATMENT PLAN.

04:53.043 --> 04:54.254
THIS ISN'T A BRAIN TUMOR
COMING BACK?

04:54.254 --> 04:55.586
I MEAN,
IT WAS SIX YEARS AGO, BUT --

04:55.586 --> 04:57.087
NO, I LOOKED
AT DR. SHEPHERD'S NOTES

04:57.087 --> 04:58.218
AND HIS FOLLOW-UP SCANS,

04:58.218 --> 04:59.550
AND I REALLY THINK
THAT YOU BEAT THAT.

04:59.550 --> 05:01.181
I THINK THIS IS
A TOTALLY SEPARATE CANCER.

05:01.181 --> 05:02.222
ARE YOU HAVING
ANY TROUBLE BREATHING?

05:02.222 --> 05:03.684
NO.

05:03.684 --> 05:06.387
SHE HAS DECREASED
BREATH SOUNDS.

05:06.387 --> 05:08.599
LET'S ADD A CONTRAST STUDY
TO THAT STAGING C.T.

05:08.599 --> 05:09.980
WHY?
WHAT DO YOU THINK IT IS?

05:09.980 --> 05:12.563
UH, THE CONTRAST JUST GIVES US
MORE OF A DETAILED LOOK.

05:12.563 --> 05:14.355
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

05:14.355 --> 05:16.777
UM, YEAH, YOU KNOW,
AND IT'LL GIVE YOUR TOES

05:16.777 --> 05:18.819
A CHANCE TO DRY
BEFORE THE BIOPSY.

05:18.819 --> 05:20.150
PERFECT.
YEAH.

05:21.902 --> 05:23.444
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:24.945 --> 05:26.947
[ SIREN WAILING ]

05:26.947 --> 05:28.909
WHAT DO WE GOT?

05:28.909 --> 05:31.872
LISA CAMPBELL, 32,
FOUND IN APARTMENT TRASH CHUTE.

05:31.872 --> 05:34.294
COMPACTOR TORE HER LEG UP
PRETTY GOOD BEFORE IT JAMMED.

05:34.294 --> 05:36.216
LOST A LOT OF BLOOD
IN THE FIELD,

05:36.216 --> 05:37.548
BUT VITALS ARE STABLE.

05:37.548 --> 05:39.339
WHY WAS
SHE IN A TRASH --

05:39.339 --> 05:40.591
FORAGING FOR FOOD,
PROBABLY.

05:40.591 --> 05:42.553
HOW MANY TIMES
DO I HAVE TO TELL YOU?

05:42.553 --> 05:44.094
I'M NOT HOMELESS.
I DON'T FORAGE.

05:44.094 --> 05:45.345
I HAVE A PhD.

05:45.345 --> 05:48.639
ON MY COUNT.
ONE, TWO, THREE.

05:48.639 --> 05:51.562
OKAY, START HER ON ONE GRAM
OF CEFAZOLIN.

05:51.562 --> 05:53.774
WE NEED TO CLEAN THIS OUT.
PAGE PLASTICS.

05:53.774 --> 05:55.776
I'LL DO IT.
ALL RIGHT, LISA,

05:55.776 --> 05:57.187
IS THERE ANYONE YOU'D LIKE
FOR US TO CALL?

05:57.187 --> 05:58.278
MY BOYFRIEND.

05:58.278 --> 06:00.030
I WAS IN THAT TRASH CHUTE
FOR TWO DAYS.

06:00.030 --> 06:01.191
HE'S PROBABLY WORRIED SICK.

06:01.191 --> 06:02.242
HIS NAME IS TED.

06:02.242 --> 06:04.034
IF HIS WIFE ANSWERS,

06:04.034 --> 06:06.447
HANG UP
AND TRY AGAIN IN AN HOUR.

06:06.447 --> 06:08.659
[ SIREN WAILING ]

06:10.661 --> 06:12.122
THIS CAN'T BE LEGAL.
Richard: IT IS.

06:12.122 --> 06:14.755
THE HOSPITAL IS ALLOWED
TO CREATE ANY POLICY

06:14.755 --> 06:16.667
REGARDING CO-WORKERS DATING
THAT THEY SEE FIT.

06:16.667 --> 06:19.550
SHEPHERD MET GREY
WHILE SHE WAS AN INTERN.

06:19.550 --> 06:20.801
AND WHAT ABOUT
WARREN AND BAILEY?

06:20.801 --> 06:23.383
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
WE'RE MARRIED, SO JUST...

06:23.383 --> 06:24.384
[ SIGHS ]

06:24.384 --> 06:25.926
IF DATING CO-WORKERS
IS FROWNED UPON,

06:25.926 --> 06:27.007
HOW ARE THEY SUPPOSED TO
MEET ANYONE?

06:27.007 --> 06:28.098
I'M GOOD. YOU DON'T
HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT ME.

06:28.098 --> 06:29.720
YOU SPEND
HALF YOUR LIFE HERE, SHANE.

06:29.720 --> 06:31.472
THIS IS YOUR DATING POOL.

06:31.472 --> 06:34.725
WHY AM I THE ONLY ONE
WHO THINKS THIS IS RIDICULOUS?

06:34.725 --> 06:36.016
THEY SHOULDN'T BE ABLE
TO DO THIS TO US.

06:36.016 --> 06:38.068
NOBODY'S DOING ANYTHING
TO YOU.

06:38.068 --> 06:40.360
THIS IS BEING DONE
FOR YOU.

06:40.360 --> 06:43.113
ONE OF YOUR OWN
DIDN'T FEEL SAFE AT WORK

06:43.113 --> 06:44.324
AND LODGED
AN ANONYMOUS COMPLAINT.

06:44.324 --> 06:45.325
ONE OF OUR OWN?

06:46.987 --> 06:48.869
YOU REALIZE YOU JUST MADE
MY RELATIONSHIP ILLEGAL.

06:50.791 --> 06:52.493
PRETTY SURE HE JUST SAID
IT WAS ANONYMOUS.

06:52.493 --> 06:53.744
YEAH, RIGHT.

06:53.744 --> 06:55.626
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

06:57.538 --> 07:04.384
[ SIREN WAILS ]

07:09.219 --> 07:11.221
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

07:12.312 --> 07:13.393
THAT'S A GIANT MASS.

07:13.393 --> 07:14.685
COULD BE A MET.

07:14.685 --> 07:16.557
SHE HAD BRAIN CANCER
SIX YEARS AGO,

07:16.557 --> 07:19.480
AND TORRES IS DOING A BIOPSY
ON A POSSIBLE OSTEOSARCOMA.

07:19.480 --> 07:21.652
THREE CANCERS
BY THE RIPE, OLD AGE OF 16.

07:21.652 --> 07:22.773
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

07:22.773 --> 07:24.274
THAT'S BAD LUCK
OR SOMETHING GENETIC.

07:24.274 --> 07:25.736
BAILEY'S GONNA TEST
FOR A LINK.

07:25.736 --> 07:27.488
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
[ SIGHS ]

07:27.488 --> 07:29.069
HIGHLY INVASIVE.

07:29.069 --> 07:30.120
I DON'T THINK
YOU CAN REMOVE IT

07:30.120 --> 07:31.161
WITHOUT SHRINKING IT FIRST.

07:31.161 --> 07:32.663
WHAT IF SHE DOESN'T RESPOND
TO CHEMO?

07:32.663 --> 07:34.124
THEN WE STILL NEED
TO FIGURE OUT

07:34.124 --> 07:35.876
A SURGICAL APPROACH
THAT WON'T JUST KILL HER.

07:35.876 --> 07:39.289
WE NEED TO BE AS AGGRESSIVE
AS THIS CANCER.

07:39.289 --> 07:40.420
MM. OKAY.

07:40.420 --> 07:41.842
ALL RIGHT, FOLKS.

07:41.842 --> 07:43.544
YOU'RE GONNA STUDY HER
CASE FILES, LOOK AT THE SCANS.

07:43.544 --> 07:45.886
I WANT YOU TO COME UP WITH
A SURGICAL TREATMENT PLAN.

07:45.886 --> 07:48.639
THE BOARD DID YOU A FAVOR
WITH THIS NEW RULE.

07:48.639 --> 07:50.721
YOU'RE GONNA TAKE
ALL THAT BRAIN POWER YOU USE

07:50.721 --> 07:53.684
TO DEVOTE TO PENISES AND VAGINAS
AND PUT IT TO SOME GOOD USE.

07:53.684 --> 07:54.935
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:54.935 --> 07:57.187
UM, CAN WE, UH, USE
OTHER DOCTORS AS RESOURCES?

07:57.187 --> 07:58.268
WHAT,
LIKE YOUR WIFE?

07:58.268 --> 08:00.270
YES, YOU SHOULD,
AND YOU CAN.

08:00.270 --> 08:01.271
WORK AS A TEAM.

08:01.271 --> 08:03.023
BOUNCE IDEAS
OFF OF ONE ANOTHER.

08:03.023 --> 08:05.105
YOU COME UP WITH SOMETHING,
I'M ALL EARS.

08:05.105 --> 08:07.067
SO, UH,
YOU GUYS WANT TO START

08:07.067 --> 08:09.199
THROWING
SOME IDEAS AROUND OR...?

08:09.199 --> 08:11.281
I'M GOOD
ON MY OWN.

08:11.281 --> 08:13.283
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

08:15.115 --> 08:17.117
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

08:19.580 --> 08:20.711
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

08:20.711 --> 08:22.252
MY FLIGHT LEAVES
AT 9:00 TONIGHT.

08:22.252 --> 08:23.463
THE CAB'S
GONNA PICK ME UP HERE.

08:23.463 --> 08:24.585
THE KIDS ARE IN DAYCARE.

08:24.585 --> 08:26.256
THE LAUNDRY
IS CLEAN AND FOLDED,

08:26.256 --> 08:27.838
AND THE KITCHEN
IS FULLY STOCKED.

08:27.838 --> 08:29.299
IT'S ONE LAST INTERVIEW.

08:29.299 --> 08:31.091
YOU'VE SAID THAT
BEFORE THE LAST TWO INTERVIEWS.

08:31.091 --> 08:32.843
I KNOW. I WILL SEE YOU
BEFORE I LEAVE.

08:32.843 --> 08:34.184
WHERE YOU GOING?

08:34.184 --> 08:36.096
UH, ACTUALLY,
I HAVE ANOTHER INTERVIEW
WITH THE WHITE HOUSE.

08:36.096 --> 08:37.978
OH, SHOW-OFF.

08:37.978 --> 08:39.189
HEY,
DO YOU WANT TO SLEEP OVER?

08:39.189 --> 08:40.190
YOU CAN HELP ME
TRY AND FIGURE OUT

08:40.190 --> 08:41.401
WHY MY RESEARCH
ISN'T WORKING.

08:41.401 --> 08:42.773
AW.
AND YOU CAN HELP ME
WITH THE KIDS.

08:42.773 --> 08:44.314
MNH-MNH.
SOUNDS LIKE FRATERNIZATION.

08:44.314 --> 08:45.696
WE COULD TALK
ABOUT OWEN AND EMMA.

08:45.696 --> 08:47.147
OH, WHAT'S THERE
TO TALK ABOUT?

08:47.147 --> 08:48.278
THEY'RE MOVING IN.
WHATEVER.

08:48.278 --> 08:50.410
I HAVE WINE.

08:50.410 --> 08:51.451
I'LL BE THERE.

08:51.451 --> 08:53.203
YEAH. FIGURED.

08:53.203 --> 08:54.534
Miranda: FOR YOU.

08:54.534 --> 08:57.157
SO, WE'RE SUPPOSED TO FILL
THIS WHOLE THING UP WITH SPIT?

08:57.157 --> 08:58.579
NO. TO THE LINE.

08:58.579 --> 09:00.210
HOW?

09:00.210 --> 09:03.624
THINK ABOUT
DILL PICKLES.

09:03.624 --> 09:05.165
OH, MY GOD.
IT WORKS.

09:05.165 --> 09:07.167
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
EVERY TIME.

09:07.167 --> 09:09.129
AND THIS IS GOING
TO TELL YOU...?

09:09.129 --> 09:11.381
IF THERE'S A GENETIC REASON

09:11.381 --> 09:13.263
WHY YOU ALL
KEEP GETTING CANCER.

09:13.263 --> 09:15.305
WELL, IT'S GOT TO BE
IN MY WIFE'S SIDE.

09:15.305 --> 09:16.556
THERE'S BEEN
A COUPLE OF BREAST,

09:16.556 --> 09:18.979
A PANCREAS, A LUNG,
AND A BUTT.

09:18.979 --> 09:21.181
OH,
AND BILLY'S BALLS.

09:21.181 --> 09:23.063
BUT WE KEEP SURVIVING.

09:23.063 --> 09:24.314
WE BEAT CANCER.

09:24.314 --> 09:25.445
YEP.

09:25.445 --> 09:27.187
THAT'S WHAT WE DO.

09:27.187 --> 09:29.189
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

09:29.189 --> 09:31.281
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

09:31.281 --> 09:33.784
Jackson:
GO AHEAD AND ALERT THE O.R.
I HAVE A DEBRIDE LEG REPAIR.

09:33.784 --> 09:34.905
RIGHT AWAY, DOCTOR.

09:34.905 --> 09:35.906
Pam: GOD, LISA.

09:35.906 --> 09:37.157
I TOLD YOU NOT TO COME
TO THE PARTY.

09:37.157 --> 09:39.199
I ALSO TOLD YOU
NOT TO HAVE A SECRET AFFAIR

09:39.199 --> 09:40.621
WITH THE HEAD OF THE SOCIOLOGY
DEPARTMENT, BY THE WAY.

09:40.621 --> 09:42.582
I KNOW. I KNOW.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

09:42.582 --> 09:44.374
BUT, YOU KNOW,
I WASN'T GOING TO GO,

09:44.374 --> 09:46.006
BUT THEN EVERYONE
FROM THE DEPARTMENT WAS GOING.

09:46.006 --> 09:48.048
IT WOULD HAVE LOOKED STRANGE
IF I WASN'T THERE.
REALLY?

09:48.048 --> 09:50.210
YOU DON'T THINK GETTING STUCK
IN HIS TRASH CHUTE

09:50.210 --> 09:51.712
WITH A PIECE OF FISH
IN YOUR HAIR

09:51.712 --> 09:53.764
LOOKS MORE STRANGE
THAN NOT GOING TO A PARTY?

09:53.764 --> 09:54.805
MNH-MNH.

09:54.805 --> 09:56.306
HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?

09:56.306 --> 09:58.518
WELL, YOU KNOW,
HE IGNORED ME ALL NIGHT,

09:58.518 --> 10:00.310
WHICH MAYBE I'M --
I'M USED TO

10:00.310 --> 10:01.982
BECAUSE THAT'S HOW WE ARE
IN PUBLIC.

10:01.982 --> 10:03.814
BUT AFTER A WHILE,
I JUST --

10:03.814 --> 10:05.395
[ SIGHS ]
I COULDN'T TAKE IT ANYMORE.

10:05.395 --> 10:08.148
SO, I GRABBED MY COAT
AND MADE A BREAK FOR THE DOOR,

10:08.148 --> 10:10.400
BUT JUST AS I WAS
ABOUT TO LEAVE,

10:10.400 --> 10:14.324
HE CALLED MY NAME,
AND I STOPPED BECAUSE --

10:14.324 --> 10:15.325
FINALLY.

10:16.196 --> 10:18.739
BUT ALL HE DID WAS ASK
IF I'D MIND

10:18.739 --> 10:20.370
THROWING OUT THE TRASH
ON MY WAY OUT.

10:20.370 --> 10:22.332
AND I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY,

10:22.332 --> 10:27.087
SO I-I-I TOOK THE BAG,
THE BIG, SMELLY TRASH BAG,

10:27.087 --> 10:29.129
AND I TOSSED IT
IN THE CHUTE.

10:29.129 --> 10:31.421
BUT I WAS SO MORTIFIED
BECAUSE I DIDN'T REALIZE

10:31.421 --> 10:34.014
I HAD THROWN MY PURSE
ALONG WITH IT.

10:34.014 --> 10:35.255
SO, YOU JUMPED IN AFTER IT?

10:35.255 --> 10:37.307
OH, I CLEARLY MAKE
EXCELLENT CHOICES.

10:38.388 --> 10:40.220
DOES TED KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED?

10:40.220 --> 10:41.852
NO. I DIDN'T TELL HIM.

10:41.852 --> 10:44.024
I WAS TRYING TO PRESERVE
YOUR DIGNITY.
THANK YOU.

10:44.024 --> 10:46.186
I DIDN'T REALIZE THERE WAS
NOTHING LEFT TO PRESERVE.

10:46.186 --> 10:48.689
UM, WELL, I CERTAINLY CAN'T DO
ANYTHING ABOUT YOUR DIGNITY,

10:48.689 --> 10:50.360
BUT IF WE'RE GONNA PRESERVE
THIS LEG,

10:50.360 --> 10:52.402
WE NEED TO GET YOU
RIGHT UP TO THE O.R.

10:52.402 --> 10:53.864
[ SIGHS ]

10:53.864 --> 10:54.985
IS THAT A SHRIMP TAIL?

10:54.985 --> 10:56.697
Lisa:
OH, NO, THAT'S A PRAWN.

10:56.697 --> 10:59.539
TED'S WIFE PREPARED THEM.

10:59.539 --> 11:01.241
[ Voice breaking ]
THEY WERE ACTUALLY REALLY GOOD.

11:01.241 --> 11:03.413
OH, MY GOD.

11:06.666 --> 11:08.248
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

11:08.248 --> 11:09.459
WELL,
THE PRELIM PATH REPORT

11:09.459 --> 11:10.791
LOOKS LIKE
HIGH-GRADE OSTEOSARCOMA.

11:10.791 --> 11:12.753
BUT WE'LL NEED ANOTHER DAY
TO GET THE FINAL REPORT.

11:12.753 --> 11:14.965
WE STILL NEED TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT'S GOING ON IN HER CHEST.

11:14.965 --> 11:15.966
YEAH.

11:15.966 --> 11:17.177
HEY!
DID YOU SHOW KEPNER?

11:17.177 --> 11:18.799
NO, NO, NO, SHE'S WORKING
WITH AVERY ALL DAY,

11:18.799 --> 11:19.850
SO I DIDN'T WANT TO BRAG.

11:19.850 --> 11:20.931
AH, GOOD CALL.
YEAH.

11:20.931 --> 11:22.222
BUT THEN WE HAD COFFEE,
AND IT SPARKLED,

11:22.222 --> 11:23.804
SO I ENDED UP, YOU KNOW,
SHOWING IT OFF, ANYWAY.

11:23.804 --> 11:25.395
[ LAUGHS ]
THERE WERE --
THERE WERE SQUEALS.

11:25.395 --> 11:27.267
HEY, KAREV, DO YOU NOTICE
ANYTHING DIFFERENT ABOUT ME?

11:27.267 --> 11:28.268
NO.

11:28.268 --> 11:29.359
CALLIE GAVE IT TO ME.

11:29.359 --> 11:30.811
WE'RE TRYING TO UNPACK
A BOX A DAY.

11:30.811 --> 11:32.362
SO, THIS MORNING,
CALLIE WAS --

11:32.362 --> 11:34.524
HEY, YOU KNOW,
MOST PEOPLE AT LEAST PRETEND

11:34.524 --> 11:35.986
TO LIKE THIS STORY, SO --

11:35.986 --> 11:38.318
Jo: ALEX, YOU CAN'T KEEP
IGNORING MY PAGES.

11:38.318 --> 11:39.449
WE REALLY NEED TO TALK.

11:39.449 --> 11:40.911
NOT NOW.
IF NOT NOW, WHEN?

11:40.911 --> 11:42.412
WE CAN'T SNEAK OFF TO HAVE
A PRIVATE CONVERSATION.

11:42.412 --> 11:43.533
IT'S FORBIDDEN!

11:43.533 --> 11:46.166
OH, WILL YOU STOP?
IT'S JUST A STUPID RULE.

11:46.166 --> 11:47.707
NOBODY'S TAKING IT
SERIOUSLY.

11:47.707 --> 11:49.209
I'M TAKING IT SERIOUSLY.

11:49.209 --> 11:50.500
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT IT
BECAUSE YOU HAVE SENIORITY,

11:50.500 --> 11:51.962
BUT I'M A RESIDENT.

11:51.962 --> 11:54.464
THIS IS MY REPUTATION
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT, MY CAREER.

11:54.464 --> 11:56.096
I KNOW THAT YOU THINK
THE RULE IS CRAP,

11:56.096 --> 11:57.507
BUT WE CAN'T JUST IGNORE IT
AT MY EXPENSE.

11:57.507 --> 11:58.839
Alex:
YOU'RE OVERREACTING!

11:58.839 --> 11:59.970
NO, I'M NOT!

11:59.970 --> 12:01.341
OH, SO, WHAT,
YOU'RE JUST GONNA ROLL OVER

12:01.341 --> 12:03.103
AND LET THE HOSPITAL TELL YOU
WHO YOU CAN BE WITH?

12:03.103 --> 12:04.144
THERE ISN'T A CHOICE.

12:04.144 --> 12:05.475
THERE'S ALWAYS A CHOICE!

12:05.475 --> 12:08.268
YOU CAN CHOOSE TO MAKE THE BEST
OUT OF A BAD SITUATION.

12:08.268 --> 12:09.519
YOU CAN CHOOSE
TO ACT LIKE AN ADULT.

12:09.519 --> 12:11.351
YOU CAN CHOOSE
NOT TO PICK A FIGHT

12:11.351 --> 12:12.813
IN FRONT OF
THE ENTIRE HOSPITAL.

12:12.813 --> 12:14.194
YOU WANT
TO WALK AROUND HERE

12:14.194 --> 12:16.236
AND PRETEND LIKE WE DON'T
MEAN ANYTHING TO EACH OTHER?

12:16.236 --> 12:17.858
FINE.
I'LL MAKE IT EASY FOR YOU.

12:17.858 --> 12:19.529
WE DON'T MEAN ANYTHING
TO EACH OTHER,

12:19.529 --> 12:20.530
NOT ANYMORE,
'CAUSE WE'RE DONE!

12:20.530 --> 12:22.202
[ Voice breaking ]
THAT IS NOT WHAT I WANT.

12:22.202 --> 12:23.743
OH, SCREW IT!
ALEX!

12:23.743 --> 12:25.575
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

12:27.037 --> 12:28.418
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

12:28.418 --> 12:30.040
ARE YOU OKAY?

12:33.543 --> 12:35.465
HMM.

12:35.465 --> 12:36.927
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]
[ INHALES SHARPLY, SNIFFLES ]

12:36.927 --> 12:37.928
HEY.

12:37.928 --> 12:38.929
HOW WAS THAT?

12:38.929 --> 12:40.510
ALARMINGLY CONVINCING.

12:40.510 --> 12:42.762
[ CHUCKLES ]
JUST STOP FREAKING OUT, OKAY?

12:42.762 --> 12:43.763
NOW I WILL.

12:43.763 --> 12:45.145
THANKS FOR DOING THAT
FOR ME.

12:45.145 --> 12:46.807
I'LL SEE YOU TONIGHT.

12:53.563 --> 12:55.655
[ SIREN WAILING ]

12:57.737 --> 12:59.860
YOU KNOW, I APPRECIATE
THE DINNER DATE,

12:59.860 --> 13:03.243
BUT I THOUGHT WEBBER TOLD
YOU PEOPLE TO WORK TOGETHER.

13:03.243 --> 13:05.075
[ CHUCKLES ] WE'RE NOT
GONNA GET ANYWHERE THAT WAY.

13:05.075 --> 13:08.538
I-I KNOW
THIS NON-FRATERNIZATION POLICY

13:08.538 --> 13:09.830
IS GONNA BE BENEFICIAL
IN THE LONG RUN,

13:09.830 --> 13:12.712
BUT FOR NOW,
IT JUST GIVES THOSE KIDS

13:12.712 --> 13:14.915
ONE MORE REASON
TO SHUT ME OUT.

13:14.915 --> 13:18.879
UM, JUST WHO ARE YOU TRYING
TO FRATERNIZE WITH?

13:18.879 --> 13:21.381
UM, MY WIFE.

13:21.381 --> 13:25.055
THEY'RE MAD AT ME
BECAUSE I GET TO BE HAPPY.

13:25.055 --> 13:27.637
MM.

13:27.637 --> 13:28.979
SEEMS HARDLY FAIR.

13:28.979 --> 13:31.061
I AGREE.

13:31.061 --> 13:36.106
BUT, UH, YOU KNOW,
THEY'RE GONNA HATE ME ANYWAY.

13:36.106 --> 13:38.608
SO, UH, MIGHT AS WELL
GET SOMETHING OUT OF IT, RIGHT?

13:38.608 --> 13:40.991
[ LAUGHS ]
BEN WARREN, WE ARE AT WORK.

13:40.991 --> 13:42.362
MM-HMM.

13:43.323 --> 13:44.494
BUT YOU CAN LOCK
THAT DOOR.

13:44.494 --> 13:45.996
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:45.996 --> 13:48.328
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:50.000 --> 13:52.542
OH, MY GOD.

13:52.542 --> 13:53.543
[ TABLE THUDS ]

13:53.543 --> 13:54.624
ALREADY? [ CHUCKLES ]

13:54.624 --> 13:56.086
I HAVEN'T EVEN
GOTTEN STARTED YET.

13:56.086 --> 13:59.009
NO, UH, THERE'S A MUTATION
IN THE p53 GENE.

13:59.009 --> 14:01.801
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

14:01.801 --> 14:03.673
[ OWL HOOTING,
INSECTS CHIRPING ]

14:03.673 --> 14:05.675
Cristina: EMMA PROBABLY KEEPS
A NICE HOME,

14:05.675 --> 14:09.769
HAS WINDOW TREATMENTS,
USES PLACE MATS.

14:09.769 --> 14:11.391
OH, PLACE MATS
ARE OVERRATED.

14:11.391 --> 14:13.473
I WANT HIM TO BE HAPPY.

14:13.473 --> 14:15.145
I'M ENJOYING
TORTURING DEREK.

14:15.145 --> 14:18.028
[ Chuckling ] DOES THAT MAKE ME
A TERRIBLE PERSON?

14:18.028 --> 14:20.070
MNH-MNH. MNH-MNH.

14:20.070 --> 14:22.983
MM.
IT'S WEIRD, THOUGH.

14:22.983 --> 14:24.614
IT'S REALLY OVER.

14:27.447 --> 14:28.448
I'M EMPTY.

14:28.448 --> 14:30.080
YEP.

14:30.080 --> 14:32.162
THAT WINDOW IS CLOSING.

14:32.162 --> 14:35.875
SHE IS GONNA GIVE HIM
BABIES,

14:35.875 --> 14:38.548
AND THEN HE'S GONNA BE
SOMEBODY'S DADDY.

14:38.548 --> 14:41.211
AND THEN
IT'S REALLY OVER.

14:41.211 --> 14:43.924
BUT YOU GUYS ARE DIVORCED
AND SEEING OTHER PEOPLE.

14:43.924 --> 14:46.967
DOESN'T THAT MEAN
IT'S REALLY OVER, ANYWAY?

14:46.967 --> 14:48.008
OH, COME ON.

14:48.008 --> 14:50.010
YOU SHOULD KNOW
BETTER THAN ANYONE

14:50.010 --> 14:51.561
THAT THAT IS NOT TRUE.

14:51.561 --> 14:53.473
BUT SOMEBODY'S DADDY?

14:53.473 --> 14:56.476
YOU KIND OF CAN'T GET
BETWEEN THAT.

14:58.188 --> 15:01.611
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
ON A PLANE.

15:01.611 --> 15:04.284
THEY CALLED ME BEFORE
I EVEN LEFT TO GO TO THE AIRPORT

15:04.284 --> 15:07.487
AND CANCELLED THE INTERVIEW.

15:07.487 --> 15:09.029
WELL,
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

15:09.029 --> 15:10.530
THE PRESIDENT DUMPED HIM.

15:10.530 --> 15:11.581
Shh!
OH.

15:11.581 --> 15:13.413
YOU KNOW, I'M OUT.
I'M OUT.

15:13.413 --> 15:16.166
YOU GUYS, UH, HAVE, UH,
A GOOD NIGHT.

15:16.166 --> 15:18.128
I'M CATCHING A CAB.

15:18.128 --> 15:20.800
BYE, BYE, BYE.
KISS TO THE GIRLS.

15:22.592 --> 15:24.094
I THINK I'M GONNA TURN IN.
[ SIGHS ]

15:24.094 --> 15:26.676
YOU DON'T KNOW
THAT IT'S OVER.

15:26.676 --> 15:28.758
WHAT DID THEY SAY?

15:28.758 --> 15:31.311
I BETTER TURN IN.

15:32.852 --> 15:34.854
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

15:37.317 --> 15:38.938
CONGRATULATIONS!

15:38.938 --> 15:40.230
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

15:40.230 --> 15:42.022
I HEARD YOU'RE MOVING...

15:42.022 --> 15:43.773
IN WITH EMMA!

15:43.773 --> 15:46.156
UM, YEAH.

15:46.156 --> 15:47.157
WE MIGHT, YEAH.

15:47.157 --> 15:49.119
YEAH, SO I BROUGHT YOU
SOME WINE!

15:49.119 --> 15:50.200
WHOA, WHAT -- [ CHUCKLES ]

15:50.200 --> 15:52.742
WAIT. THIS IS A VERY NICE
BOTTLE OF WINE.

15:52.742 --> 15:53.913
YEAH, I KNOW.

15:53.913 --> 15:55.165
UH, UH, I SWIPED IT
FROM DEREK'S COLLECTION.

15:55.165 --> 15:56.496
IT LOOKED
REALLY EXPENSIVE.

15:56.496 --> 15:57.497
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:57.497 --> 15:59.209
[ SIGHS ] SO, ENJOY!

15:59.209 --> 16:00.460
[ LAUGHS ]
THE BOTH OF YOU.

16:00.460 --> 16:02.542
OH, NO, EMMA'S --
SHE'S NOT HERE.

16:02.542 --> 16:05.135
OH.
[ OWL HOOTING ]

16:05.135 --> 16:06.546
Jo:
SO, WHAT'S THE PLAN NOW?

16:06.546 --> 16:09.349
SHOULD I START SNEAKING IN
YOUR BEDROOM WINDOW?

16:09.349 --> 16:11.011
YOU -- YOU DO LIVE
WITH ONE OF THE BOARD MEMBERS.

16:11.011 --> 16:12.552
I TOLD YOU --
SHE'S AT MER'S.

16:12.552 --> 16:14.394
YEAH, I'M NOT JUST TALKING
ABOUT TONIGHT.

16:14.394 --> 16:16.266
LOOK.
THINGS WILL BLOW OVER.

16:16.266 --> 16:19.189
I'LL WORK ON MER AND CRISTINA.
THIS WILL ALL GO AWAY.

16:19.189 --> 16:20.400
UNTIL THEN, YEAH,

16:20.400 --> 16:22.982
MAYBE YOU SNEAK IN
MY BEDROOM WINDOW.

16:22.982 --> 16:28.318
BUT YANG'S SUPPOSED TO BE OUT
ALL NIGHT TONIGHT.

16:28.318 --> 16:30.280
YEAH.
YOU WANT TO GO UPSTAIRS?

16:30.280 --> 16:33.453
I WOULD, BUT UPSTAIRS
IS JUST SO FAR AWAY.

16:41.081 --> 16:42.332
HI.

16:42.332 --> 16:44.424
I GOT SO MANY COMPLIMENTS
ON MY RING TODAY.

16:44.424 --> 16:45.425
OOH.

16:45.425 --> 16:46.586
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:46.586 --> 16:47.837
[ SMOOCHES ]

16:47.837 --> 16:50.590
IT'S SO SAD, THOUGH,
ABOUT ALEX AND WILSON.

16:50.590 --> 16:52.182
OH, YEAH.
MMM.

16:52.182 --> 16:56.806
IT'S NOT FAIR, RIGHT,
THAT WE GET TO BE SO HAPPY

16:56.806 --> 16:58.268
AND OTHER PEOPLE
HAVE TO BE SO MISERABLE?

16:58.268 --> 17:00.190
YEAH, LIKE APRIL --
JUST OUT IN THE COLD.

17:00.190 --> 17:02.102
MMM. MMM.

17:02.102 --> 17:03.353
I FEEL TERRIBLE.

17:03.353 --> 17:04.444
AWFUL.

17:04.444 --> 17:05.525
MMM.

17:05.525 --> 17:06.696
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

17:06.696 --> 17:08.238
WHO AM I
GONNA SLEEP WITH?

17:08.238 --> 17:09.359
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:09.359 --> 17:10.780
THE -- THE HOSPITAL
IS MY DATING POOL.

17:10.780 --> 17:11.911
MM-HMM.

17:11.911 --> 17:15.155
YOU -- YOU ARE MAKING IT
IMPOSSIBLE

17:15.155 --> 17:16.866
FOR ME TO GET LAID.

17:16.866 --> 17:19.289
WELL, I DON'T THINK THAT
HAS EVER BEEN A PROBLEM.

17:19.289 --> 17:20.580
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

17:20.580 --> 17:23.213
YEAH, WELL...

17:23.213 --> 17:25.085
MMM.

17:25.085 --> 17:26.336
WERE YOU SAD

17:26.336 --> 17:28.428
THERE WEREN'T ANY WINDOW
TREATMENTS AT THE FIREHOUSE?

17:28.428 --> 17:29.799
WHAT?

17:29.799 --> 17:32.672
YOU KNOW,
DRAPES AND, UH,

17:32.672 --> 17:34.264
THE THING THAT GOES
ON TOP OF IT.

17:34.264 --> 17:35.845
UH...
WHAT ARE THEY CALLED?

17:35.845 --> 17:37.177
IT'S A --
CURTAIN ROD?

17:37.177 --> 17:39.099
MNH-MNH. NO.

17:39.099 --> 17:40.640
I MEAN, YES,
OBVIOUSLY YOU NEED THAT,

17:40.640 --> 17:42.682
BUT THERE'S
THAT OTHER THING.

17:42.682 --> 17:44.394
[ SIGHS ]
I SHOULD KNOW THIS.

17:44.394 --> 17:46.486
MY MOTHER
IS AN INTERIOR DECORATOR.

17:46.486 --> 17:47.687
I SPENT MY CHILDHOOD

17:47.687 --> 17:50.190
LISTENING TO HER TALK
ABOUT THESE THINGS.

17:50.190 --> 17:51.451
WHO ARE YOU --
ARE YOU --

17:51.451 --> 17:52.992
MOM? HEY, IT'S ME.

17:52.992 --> 17:54.954
YES.
YEAH, I KNOW IT'S LATE.

17:54.954 --> 17:56.536
NO, I'M FINE.

17:56.536 --> 17:58.408
LISTEN, UH,
WHAT DO YOU CALL,

17:58.408 --> 18:02.582
UH, THOSE THINGS
THAT ARE ON TOP OF YOUR WINDOWS?

18:02.582 --> 18:04.204
NO, THE OTHER THING.

18:04.204 --> 18:06.796
VALANCE! YES!

18:06.796 --> 18:08.548
THANK YOU.
OKAY, GOOD NIGHT.

18:08.548 --> 18:10.049
[ CELLPHONE THUDS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:10.049 --> 18:11.301
VALANCE.

18:11.301 --> 18:13.052
WERE YOU -- WERE YOU SAD

18:13.052 --> 18:14.764
WE -- WE --
WE NEVER HAD VALANCES?

18:14.764 --> 18:15.845
[ Chuckling ] NO.

18:15.845 --> 18:16.886
NO.
A LITTLE BIT?

18:16.886 --> 18:19.098
NO. NO.

18:19.098 --> 18:22.772
I'M NOT SAD...

18:22.772 --> 18:24.063
THAT WE DIDN'T HAVE
VALANCES.

18:24.063 --> 18:26.356
♪ UNTIL IT ENDS ♪

18:26.356 --> 18:29.189
♪ THERE IS NO END ♪

18:29.189 --> 18:34.364
♪ KEEP WITH ME FORWARD
ALL THROUGH THE NIGHT ♪

18:34.364 --> 18:39.329
♪ AND ONCE WE START,
THE METER CLICKS ♪

18:39.329 --> 18:42.542
♪ AND GOES RUNNING
ALL THROUGH THE NIGHT ♪

18:42.542 --> 18:46.296
IT NEVER OCCURRED TO ME,
YOU KNOW,

18:46.296 --> 18:47.587
TO GET WINDOW TREATMENTS.

18:47.587 --> 18:49.549
♪ THERE IS NO END ♪

18:49.549 --> 18:52.342
♪ KEEP WITH ME FORWARD ♪
I KNOW.

18:52.342 --> 18:56.135
♪ ALL THROUGH THE NIGHT ♪

19:00.850 --> 19:06.396
♪ KEEP WITH ME
ALL THROUGH THE NIGHT ♪

19:16.576 --> 19:17.947
I'LL PUT THEM IN FOR YOU.

19:17.947 --> 19:19.078
GREAT.
THANK YOU.

19:19.078 --> 19:21.040
HEY, SORRY I COULDN'T
COME BY LAST NIGHT.
HEY.

19:21.040 --> 19:23.162
OH, NO, NO,
IT'S -- IT'S -- IT'S FINE.

19:23.162 --> 19:24.163
I HAD THREE SURGERIES,

19:24.163 --> 19:26.456
INCLUDING AN EMERGENCY "C"
AT 28 WEEKS.

19:26.456 --> 19:27.457
BABY'S FINE.

19:27.457 --> 19:28.668
OH, THAT'S GREAT.

19:28.668 --> 19:30.129
YEAH, IT IS.
IT WAS.

19:30.129 --> 19:32.131
AND SO ARE YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:32.131 --> 19:36.135
AND I WANTED
TO SAY SOMETHING IN PERSON,

19:36.135 --> 19:38.428
UM, BUT I'M --

19:38.428 --> 19:40.600
OKAY, I'M JUST NERVOUS,
SO I'M JUST GONNA SAY IT.

19:40.600 --> 19:42.011
SO, WE'RE GONNA LOOK
AT HOUSES,

19:42.011 --> 19:44.063
AND THERE'S GONNA BE
THAT AWKWARD CONVERSATION

19:44.063 --> 19:45.895
ABOUT HOW MANY BEDROOMS
WE NEED,

19:45.895 --> 19:47.647
AWKWARD BECAUSE
THIS IS KIND OF NEW

19:47.647 --> 19:49.649
AND WE HAVEN'T REALLY TALKED
ABOUT KIDS,

19:49.649 --> 19:53.192
AND HOUSES HAVE BEDROOMS,
AND KIDS GO IN BEDROOMS.

19:53.192 --> 19:55.194
SO, UM, OKAY,
I'M JUST GONNA --

19:55.194 --> 19:56.195
[ CLAPS HANDS ]

19:56.195 --> 19:58.318
I WOULD LIKE TWO KIDS,
MAYBE THREE,

19:58.318 --> 20:03.283
AND I PLAN ON NOT WORKING
UNTIL THEY'RE IN SCHOOL

20:03.283 --> 20:07.126
AND BEING THE KIND OF MOM
THAT WALKS THEM TO SCHOOL,

20:07.126 --> 20:09.629
SO I NEED
A GOOD SCHOOL DISTRICT.

20:11.251 --> 20:13.713
I'M FREAKING YOU OUT.

20:13.713 --> 20:15.635
UM --
CRAP.

20:15.635 --> 20:17.337
WHEN I WENT OVER THIS
IN THE CAR,

20:17.337 --> 20:22.262
UH, IT DIDN'T SOUND SO
"MARRY ME AND SIRE MY CHILDREN."

20:22.262 --> 20:23.643
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT WAS REASONABLE.

20:23.643 --> 20:26.396
NO, IT --

20:26.396 --> 20:29.108
IT IS.

20:29.108 --> 20:30.940
YOU SHOULD BE TALKING
ABOUT THIS STUFF.

20:30.940 --> 20:32.191
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
GOOD.

20:32.191 --> 20:33.403
HMM.
I'M NOT CRAZY.

20:33.403 --> 20:35.945
MNH-MNH, NO,
YOU'RE NOT CRAZY.

20:35.945 --> 20:37.817
OKAY, THEN.

20:37.817 --> 20:39.319
SO, I'LL MEET YOU
BACK HERE TONIGHT,

20:39.319 --> 20:40.660
AND WE'LL GO
TO THE REAL-ESTATE AGENT.

20:40.660 --> 20:42.201
YEAH.
OKAY.

20:42.201 --> 20:44.914
[ SMOOCHES ]
BYE.

20:47.827 --> 20:49.369
IT'S TIME TO RETHINK
THE PLAN.

20:49.369 --> 20:50.830
HEY.
WHAT DID YOU FIND?

20:50.830 --> 20:54.584
OH, RORY HAS
LI-FRAUMENI SYNDROME.

20:54.584 --> 20:56.336
LI FOR WHAT?
NEVER EVEN
HEARD OF IT.

20:56.336 --> 20:57.427
NEITHER HAD I.

20:57.427 --> 20:59.549
IT'S AN EXTREMELY RARE
GENETIC CONDITION

20:59.549 --> 21:03.052
DUE TO A MUTATION
IN THE p53 GENE

21:03.052 --> 21:05.935
THAT SUPPRESSES THE ABILITY
TO REGULATE CELL GROWTH.

21:05.935 --> 21:07.266
THE POOR KID
CAN'T FIGHT OFF TUMORS.

21:07.266 --> 21:10.189
SO, AS SOON AS YOU CURE
ONE CANCER, ANOTHER ONE POPS UP.

21:10.189 --> 21:11.561
YEAH.
THAT'S AWESOME.

21:11.561 --> 21:13.152
NOW, I'M MEETING
WITH THE FAMILY TODAY.

21:13.152 --> 21:14.273
I'D LIKE TO BE ABLE
TO TELL THEM

21:14.273 --> 21:15.945
WE HAVE SOME SORT OF PLAN
IN PLACE FOR RORY.

21:15.945 --> 21:17.607
OKAY, SO, THAT CHEST TUMOR
MIGHT NOT EVEN BE A MET

21:17.607 --> 21:18.778
FROM THE OSTEOSARCOMA.

21:18.778 --> 21:20.450
THAT MAKES CHEMO
THAT MUCH MORE COMPLICATED.

21:20.450 --> 21:22.402
OKAY, THE TUMOR IN HER LEG
SHOULD RESPOND

21:22.402 --> 21:24.163
TO DOXORUBICIN,
PLUS CISPLATIN.

21:24.163 --> 21:25.405
RADIATION'S OUT.

21:25.405 --> 21:27.867
IT WOULD MAKE HER
TOO SUSCEPTIBLE TO NEW TUMORS.

21:27.867 --> 21:29.208
THE CHEST TUMOR'S
SO VASCULAR,

21:29.208 --> 21:30.670
EVEN A BIOPSY
WOULD BE PUSHING OUR LUCK.

21:30.670 --> 21:32.872
HOW RARE IS THIS?

21:32.872 --> 21:36.085
ONLY A FEW HUNDRED FAMILIES
ARE REPORTED IN THE LITERATURE.

21:36.085 --> 21:37.216
WE NEED
THOSE CASE STUDIES,

21:37.216 --> 21:39.629
BUT, I MEAN,
THAT COULD TAKE AWHILE.

21:39.629 --> 21:42.301
NOT IF I GET
THOSE RESIDENTS ON IT.

21:45.685 --> 21:47.387
SORRY I'M LATE.
I'M DOING SCUT FOR HUNT.

21:47.387 --> 21:49.429
WELL, IT'LL GET HANDLED.
THIS IS MORE IMPORTANT.

21:49.429 --> 21:50.560
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN UP.

21:50.560 --> 21:52.352
YOUR ASSIGNMENT'S CHANGED.

21:52.352 --> 21:54.273
RORY HAS
LI-FRAUMENI SYNDROME.

21:54.273 --> 21:55.855
IT'S RARE.

21:55.855 --> 21:57.817
DIG UP EVERY CASE OF IT
YOU CAN FIND.

21:57.817 --> 21:59.148
FIND OUT WHAT WORKED,
WHAT DIDN'T.

21:59.148 --> 22:01.150
I WANT ONE OF YOU TO LOOK
FOR DR. KAREV.

22:01.150 --> 22:02.402
HE'S WITH THE ONCOLOGIST.

22:02.402 --> 22:04.283
I WILL.
ARE YOU SURE?

22:04.283 --> 22:06.325
YEAH.
GOT TO FACE HIM SOMETIME.

22:07.947 --> 22:11.210
NOW, YOU CAN'T RELY
SOLELY ON THE INTERNET.

22:11.210 --> 22:13.543
HIT THE LIBRARY.

22:14.914 --> 22:16.756
NOW.

22:18.297 --> 22:20.089
UH, ROSS, A WORD?

22:23.673 --> 22:25.515
YOU'VE BEEN QUIET.

22:25.515 --> 22:28.347
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON IN YOUR HEAD,

22:28.347 --> 22:30.269
BUT IF IT'S TOO SOON
TO COME BACK FULL TIME,

22:30.269 --> 22:32.231
WE CAN TALK.
NO.

22:32.231 --> 22:34.394
JUST TRYING TO KEEP MY HEAD DOWN
AND WORK, SIR.

22:34.394 --> 22:36.315
WELL, IF YOU FEEL LIKE
YOU HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY,

22:36.315 --> 22:37.567
SPEAK UP, SON.

22:37.567 --> 22:40.069
KEEPING IT INSIDE WON'T HELP
YOU OR ANYONE ELSE.

22:40.069 --> 22:42.071
THE LAST TIME I SPOKE UP,
A PATIENT NEARLY DIED.

22:42.071 --> 22:44.323
THAT WAS GRIEF
AND EXHAUSTION TALKING.

22:45.655 --> 22:47.537
I'D LIKE TO HEAR YOU TALK.

22:53.292 --> 22:55.044
THANK YOU.
OF COURSE.

22:55.044 --> 22:57.296
YOU SHOULD PUT ME BACK
IN O.R. ROTATION.

22:57.296 --> 22:58.998
START CLIPPING ANEURYSMS
AGAIN.

22:58.998 --> 23:00.670
DEREK.
HEY.

23:00.670 --> 23:02.341
DR. HUNT.

23:03.963 --> 23:05.465
WELL, IT WOULD BE GOOD
TO HAVE YOU BACK.

23:05.465 --> 23:07.266
IT USED TO BE
ALL I WANTED TO DO.

23:07.266 --> 23:09.809
I'M GRATEFUL THAT THEY
APPROACHED ME FOR THE PROJECT

23:09.809 --> 23:11.060
AND THAT YOU
PUSHED ME TOWARDS IT.

23:11.060 --> 23:12.472
IT WASN'T ABOUT WASHINGTON
OR THE ACCOLADES.

23:12.472 --> 23:13.683
THEY'RE LOOKING
FOR ANSWERS

23:13.683 --> 23:15.775
TO QUESTIONS I'VE BEEN ASKING
MY WHOLE CAREER.

23:15.775 --> 23:17.567
AND TO KNOW THAT THAT PROJECT
IS OUT THERE --

23:17.567 --> 23:19.318
I MEAN, HOW DO I GO BACK
TO BEING SATISFIED

23:19.318 --> 23:20.399
DOING NEUROSURGERY AGAIN?

23:20.399 --> 23:21.360
YEAH.

23:21.360 --> 23:22.401
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

23:22.401 --> 23:24.904
YOUR STANDARDS
HAVE CHANGED.

23:24.904 --> 23:26.526
YEAH.

23:26.526 --> 23:28.287
MY STANDARDS HAVE CHANGED.

23:28.287 --> 23:30.830
[ SIGHS ]

23:30.830 --> 23:32.662
[ LIQUID WHIRRING ]

23:32.662 --> 23:34.624
WE WERE ABLE
TO CLEAN IT OUT IN SURGERY,

23:34.624 --> 23:37.497
AND NOW WE'RE GONNA LET THIS
VACUUM DRESSING WORK ITS MAGIC

23:37.497 --> 23:38.958
AND START
THE HEALING PROCESS.

23:38.958 --> 23:40.500
[ GASPS ]

23:40.500 --> 23:42.462
OH, MY GOD,
THOSE ARE BEAUTIFUL.

23:42.462 --> 23:43.543
DID TED SEND THEM?

23:43.543 --> 23:45.635
NO.

23:45.635 --> 23:47.306
THEY'RE FROM YOUR MOM.

23:47.306 --> 23:48.678
[ WHIMPERS ]

23:48.678 --> 23:50.760
OH, DAMN IT, LISA.
REALLY?

23:50.760 --> 23:52.552
[ Crying ]
NO, IT'S NOT TED.

23:52.552 --> 23:54.053
I MEAN, IT IS TED.

23:54.053 --> 23:55.314
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M INSANE.

23:55.314 --> 23:57.186
THIS WHOLE THING HAS MADE ME
CERTIFIABLY CRAZY.

23:57.186 --> 23:59.188
I AM A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.

23:59.188 --> 24:00.480
I'M SUPPOSED TO BE,
YOU KNOW, SMART,

24:00.480 --> 24:02.191
BUT INSTEAD I'M JUMPING
INTO TRASH CHUTES

24:02.191 --> 24:04.443
AND BURSTING INTO TEARS
BECAUSE I'M HEARTBROKEN

24:04.443 --> 24:06.445
THAT MY MOM CARES ABOUT ME
MORE THAN SOME JERK

24:06.445 --> 24:07.567
WHO WON'T EVEN TALK TO ME
IN PUBLIC!

24:07.567 --> 24:08.568
WHAT IS THAT?

24:08.568 --> 24:09.569
[ SOBS ]

24:09.569 --> 24:11.701
CAN YOU HAND ME
MY PHONE?

24:11.701 --> 24:13.623
I JUST WANT TO CALL MY MOM
AND THANK HER FOR THE FLOWERS.

24:13.623 --> 24:16.245
SURE.

24:19.458 --> 24:20.540
YOU'RE GONNA CALL TED,
AREN'T YOU?

24:26.345 --> 24:27.547
I'M A MONSTER.

24:27.547 --> 24:30.720
OH, MY GOD.
[ CRYING ]

24:34.644 --> 24:36.475
Hey, hey, hey.

24:36.475 --> 24:39.599
OH, MY GOD, WE NEED TO GO PUBLIC
WITH THIS THING, OKAY?

24:39.599 --> 24:40.600
I CAN'T KEEP TRACK

24:40.600 --> 24:43.563
OF WHEN AND WHERE I CAN PUT
MY ARMS ON MY OWN WIFE.

24:43.563 --> 24:45.655
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

24:47.316 --> 24:49.318
LOOK.
I KNOW IT'S HARD.

24:49.318 --> 24:52.111
BUT THE WHISPERS AND THE STARES
AFTER THE WEDDING

24:52.111 --> 24:53.613
HAVE JUST STARTED
TO DIE DOWN.

24:53.613 --> 24:54.704
AS SOON AS WE TELL PEOPLE,

24:54.704 --> 24:56.415
THEY'RE JUST GONNA
START UP AGAIN.
YEAH.

24:56.415 --> 25:02.291
PLUS, I LIKE OUR SECRET,
LITTLE MARRIAGE BUBBLE.

25:02.291 --> 25:05.384
SNEAKING AROUND
IS KIND OF SEXY.

25:05.384 --> 25:08.507
I AM SO PROUD
THAT YOU'RE MY WIFE.

25:08.507 --> 25:11.430
I AM MARRIED TO A BRILLIANT,
GORGEOUS TRAUMA SURGEON,

25:11.430 --> 25:14.343
AND I JUST DON'T WANT
TO HIDE IT ANYMORE, YOU KNOW?

25:14.343 --> 25:16.556
OKAY, THAT'S EVEN SEXIER.
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:16.556 --> 25:17.557
[ SIGHS ]

25:17.557 --> 25:19.559
SO [CLEARS THROAT]
WHAT DO WE DO?

25:19.559 --> 25:20.770
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

25:20.770 --> 25:22.101
I THINK WE SHOULD
START TELLING PEOPLE.

25:24.143 --> 25:25.985
IN A MORE, UH,
CONTROLLED SETTING.

25:25.985 --> 25:29.609
JUST -- DOCTOR.

25:29.609 --> 25:30.489
WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE

25:30.489 --> 25:32.531
WE'RE GONNA GET YOU STARTED
ON CHEMO SOON.

25:32.531 --> 25:35.534
I SAW MOM TALKING
TO DR. BAILEY.

25:35.534 --> 25:37.286
THERE WERE TEARS.

25:37.286 --> 25:38.287
OH, WOW.

25:38.287 --> 25:40.369
THANKS FOR THE CANCER GENES,
MOM.

25:40.369 --> 25:41.711
IF YOU HAVE IT,
I HAVE IT.

25:41.711 --> 25:44.163
OH, YOU HAVEN'T BEEN SICK
A DAY IN YOUR LIFE.

25:44.163 --> 25:45.925
YOU HAVE DAD'S NICE,
SAFE GENES.

25:45.925 --> 25:47.376
MAYBE NOT.

25:47.376 --> 25:48.588
WE'LL FIND OUT
AFTER THE TEST.

25:48.588 --> 25:51.591
YOU KNOW,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO FIND OUT

25:51.591 --> 25:53.092
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO.

25:53.092 --> 25:54.303
KNOWLEDGE SUCKS.

25:54.303 --> 25:56.095
YOUR FACE SUCKS.

25:56.095 --> 25:59.058
OH, COME ON.
I'M NOT KIDDING.

25:59.058 --> 26:01.641
I KNOW WE LIKE TO ACT
LIKE THIS ISN'T A BIG DEAL

26:01.641 --> 26:03.482
AND WE'RE THE FAMILY
THAT BEATS CANCER,

26:03.482 --> 26:07.316
BUT WE'RE NOT
ACTUALLY BEATING ANYTHING.

26:07.316 --> 26:10.449
I MEAN, LIKE, I CAN HANDLE
ONE CANCER AT A TIME,

26:10.449 --> 26:12.321
BUT IT'S ALL I SEE NOW --

26:12.321 --> 26:15.404
JUST CANCER AFTER CANCER
UNTIL I'M DEAD.

26:16.906 --> 26:19.118
AND I WISH I COULD GO BACK
AND UN-KNOW THAT.

26:21.080 --> 26:23.663
SHE CAN SAY NO, RIGHT?

26:23.663 --> 26:26.706
IT'S HER DECISION.

26:26.706 --> 26:29.669
NOT ACCORDING
TO MOM AND DAD.

26:29.669 --> 26:32.211
THEY SAY I NEED TO KNOW
BECAUSE IT'LL DETERMINE

26:32.211 --> 26:33.713
WHETHER I TAKE
AN ASPIRIN

26:33.713 --> 26:36.095
OR GET A BRAIN SCAN
FOR A HEADACHE.

26:36.095 --> 26:37.807
AND IF I'M GONNA HAVE KIDS,
I NEED TO KNOW --

26:37.807 --> 26:39.428
KIDS? YOU'RE A KID.

26:39.428 --> 26:41.520
I'M JUST SAYING, ALL RIGHT?

26:41.520 --> 26:43.602
MOM AND DAD
ARE FREAKING OUT,

26:43.602 --> 26:45.394
AND THEY'RE CALLING
THE WHOLE DAMN FAMILY

26:45.394 --> 26:47.026
AND WANTING EVERYONE
TO GET A TEST

26:47.026 --> 26:49.488
AND WANTING TO START
A FOUNDATION

26:49.488 --> 26:50.650
AND CHANGE THE WORLD

26:50.650 --> 26:53.612
AND BE LIKE THE FAMILY
THAT FIGHTS LI-FRAUMENI.

26:53.612 --> 26:56.946
WHO CARES WHAT THEY WANT?
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

26:59.538 --> 27:02.541
I CAN REALLY DECIDE
FOR MYSELF?

27:02.541 --> 27:04.163
EVEN THOUGH I'M ONLY 16

27:04.163 --> 27:05.745
AND MY PARENTS SAY
THAT I HAVE TO?

27:05.745 --> 27:09.208
I CAN SAY NO?
I CAN MAKE THE DECISION?

27:09.208 --> 27:10.629
IT'S YOUR LIFE.

27:10.629 --> 27:13.252
NOBODY CAN MAKE YOU DO ANYTHING
YOU DON'T WANT TO DO.

27:20.930 --> 27:23.763
[ WOMAN OVER P.A. SYSTEM
SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ]

27:23.763 --> 27:26.726
HEY. I NEED
THE ONCOLOGY REPORT ON RORY.

27:26.726 --> 27:28.357
THEY SAID WE SHOULD ADD
METHOTREXATE

27:28.357 --> 27:29.358
FOR THE OSTEOSARCOMA.

27:29.358 --> 27:30.569
OKAY, THANKS.
LOOK --

27:30.569 --> 27:32.031
HEY, WHAT --
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

27:32.031 --> 27:33.232
I'M DONE SNEAKING AROUND.

27:33.232 --> 27:35.324
THEY CAN'T TELL US
WHAT TO DO OR WHAT TO FEEL.

27:35.324 --> 27:36.655
IF THEY WANT TO FIRE ME,
FINE.

27:37.867 --> 27:39.238
[ SCOFFS ]

27:41.040 --> 27:42.832
WE HAD A PLAN.
WHAT HAPPENED?

27:42.832 --> 27:44.083
LOOK.
IT'S A STUPID PLAN.

27:44.083 --> 27:45.785
WE'RE ADULTS.
WE LOVE EACH OTHER.

27:45.785 --> 27:47.837
THEY CAN GO
SCREW THEMSELVES.

27:47.837 --> 27:48.838
[ METAL CLINKS ]

27:48.838 --> 27:49.879
WHAT WAS THAT?

27:49.879 --> 27:51.290
IS SOMEBODY IN THERE?

27:51.290 --> 27:52.792
HEY, GUYS.

27:52.792 --> 27:54.633
YOU WANT TO JUST HAND ME
MY SHIRT?

27:56.796 --> 27:57.596
MINE, TOO.
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

27:57.596 --> 27:59.298
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ SCOFFS ]

27:59.298 --> 28:00.509
HI.
APPRECIATE IT.

28:00.509 --> 28:01.510
UGH.

28:01.510 --> 28:03.763
COME ON.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

28:03.763 --> 28:05.304
NO!
OH!

28:06.395 --> 28:10.609
DR. WEBBER.
THIS ISN'T WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

28:20.870 --> 28:21.951
WELL, I'M FIRED.

28:21.951 --> 28:23.242
WE'RE NOT FIRED.

28:23.242 --> 28:24.663
YOU'RE NOT.
YOU'RE AN ATTENDING.

28:24.663 --> 28:26.085
I'M AN EXPENDABLE
RESIDENT.

28:26.085 --> 28:27.877
THE RULES ARE JUST
A DUMB THING ON PAPER

28:27.877 --> 28:29.208
TO COVER
THE BOARD'S ASS.

28:29.208 --> 28:30.209
NO ONE ACTUALLY CARES.

28:30.209 --> 28:31.420
WELL, SPEAKING

28:31.420 --> 28:33.252
AS THE HYPOCRITICAL
BOARD MEMBER IN THE ROOM,

28:33.252 --> 28:34.293
THE BOARD CARES.

28:34.293 --> 28:35.464
SINCE WHEN ARE YOU TWO
STILL DOING IT?

28:35.464 --> 28:36.545
SINCE THE WEDDING.

28:36.545 --> 28:38.467
NICE.

28:39.548 --> 28:40.930
WHAT?

28:40.930 --> 28:42.301
I'M DECIDING
WHETHER THIS MAKES ME

28:42.301 --> 28:43.302
HATE YOU MORE OR LESS.

28:43.302 --> 28:45.304
[ SIGHS ]
MORE.

28:45.304 --> 28:47.146
HEY, WELL, UM,
SINCE WE HAVE YOU GUYS HERE,

28:47.146 --> 28:48.768
THERE'S SOMETHING
THAT WE WANTED TO SHARE --

28:48.768 --> 28:50.059
OH, NO.

28:50.059 --> 28:51.400
THINK
HE'S STILL OUT THERE?

28:51.400 --> 28:53.692
[ SIGHS ] THERE'S ONLY
ONE WAY TO FIND OUT.

28:55.775 --> 28:57.486
[ PAGER BEEPS ]

28:59.408 --> 29:01.280
YOU GUYS WANT TO CLOSE
THE --

29:01.280 --> 29:02.782
NO?

29:04.493 --> 29:06.996
[ GIGGLES ]

29:08.577 --> 29:09.668
HEY.

29:09.668 --> 29:11.130
Meredith:
HEY. I NEED A CONSULT.

29:11.130 --> 29:12.131
OKAY.

29:12.131 --> 29:13.292
SO, MY PROJECT
IS AT A STANDSTILL

29:13.292 --> 29:15.925
UNLESS I HAND IT OVER
TO A BIOENGINEER.

29:15.925 --> 29:17.086
OKAY.

29:17.086 --> 29:18.757
WHAT'S YOUR PITCH?

29:19.638 --> 29:20.800
BECOME A BIOENGINEER.

29:22.381 --> 29:24.223
I CAN'T GIVE DEREK
THE SATISFACTION

29:24.223 --> 29:25.554
OF LIGHTENING MY WORKLOAD

29:25.554 --> 29:28.187
BECAUSE HIS GUILT
IS MY ONLY RAY OF SUNSHINE.

29:28.187 --> 29:29.558
WELL, HE DOESN'T THINK
HE'S GONNA GET THE JOB,

29:29.558 --> 29:30.769
IF THAT MAKES YOU FEEL
ANY BETTER.

29:30.769 --> 29:31.770
I KNOW.

29:31.770 --> 29:33.352
I ACTUALLY FEEL
KIND OF BAD FOR HIM.

29:33.352 --> 29:35.524
BUT I FEEL WORSE FOR ME.
I HATE QUITTING.

29:35.524 --> 29:37.486
DON'T THINK OF IT
AS QUITTING.

29:37.486 --> 29:39.698
YOU'RE WAITING FOR SCIENCE
TO CATCH UP TO YOUR BRILLIANCE.

29:39.698 --> 29:41.490
THINK OF IT AS --

29:41.490 --> 29:45.114
AS LETTING SOMEONE ELSE TAKE
YOUR PROJECT OUT FOR A SPIN.

29:45.114 --> 29:47.496
YOU JUST STEP BACK,
SEE WHAT ELSE IS OUT THERE,

29:47.496 --> 29:51.540
SO WHEN YOU COME BACK TO YOUR
PROJECT, YOU'LL HAVE FRESH EYES.

29:51.540 --> 29:55.464
IT'LL BE BETTER THAN EVER,
JUST LIKE COMING HOME.

29:55.464 --> 29:57.046
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:57.046 --> 29:58.918
YOU SLEPT WITH OWEN.

30:01.180 --> 30:03.923
YES, I DID.

30:03.923 --> 30:05.514
DON'T.

30:08.387 --> 30:10.479
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

30:10.479 --> 30:12.231
KAREV, TALK TO ME.

30:12.231 --> 30:14.193
SHE WAS HYPERTENSIVE
AND UNRESPONSIVE,

30:14.193 --> 30:15.234
WITH ABSENT BREATH SOUNDS

30:15.234 --> 30:16.986
OVER HER LEFT CHEST
WHEN I GOT HERE.

30:16.986 --> 30:18.277
I NEEDLED
FOR A TENSION PNEUMO.

30:18.277 --> 30:19.568
OKAY, WE'LL HAVE TO
GET HER INTUBATED.

30:19.568 --> 30:20.699
OKAY.

30:23.532 --> 30:24.613
Ariel: AAH!

30:24.613 --> 30:25.945
ARIEL, I NEED YOU
TO GO FIND YOUR PARENTS.

30:25.945 --> 30:27.036
[ Voice breaking ]
I COULDN'T WAKE HER UP

30:27.036 --> 30:28.707
WHEN THE MACHINE
STARTED BEEPING.

30:28.707 --> 30:30.369
I TRIED, BUT --
LOOK,
THIS IS NOT YOUR FAULT.

30:30.369 --> 30:31.830
WE'RE GONNA HELP
YOUR SISTER, OKAY?

30:31.830 --> 30:35.294
GO FIND YOUR PARENTS.
GO! NOW!

30:35.294 --> 30:37.456
WHERE THE HELL
DID ALL THIS BLOOD COME FROM?

30:37.456 --> 30:40.379
HER TUMOR COULD HAVE RUPTURED.
WE'VE GOT TO GET HER TO AN O.R.

30:40.379 --> 30:43.632
GUYS, I JUST FOUND A CASE
OF LI-FRAUMENI IN CHICAGO.

30:43.632 --> 30:46.675
THE GUY HAS ALMOST THE EXACT
SAME TYPES OF CANCERS AS RORY.

30:46.675 --> 30:49.678
UH, THEY TRIED NEOADJUVANT CHEMO
TO SHRINK IT,

30:49.678 --> 30:51.730
THEN SURGERY, AND THEN, UH...

30:51.730 --> 30:53.102
AND?

30:53.102 --> 30:55.144
AND THEN HE DIED.
[ DOOR OPENS ]

30:57.316 --> 30:59.528
I'M REALLY SORRY
FOR WHAT I'M ABOUT TO SAY,

30:59.528 --> 31:02.071
AND I WANT YOU TO KNOW THAT
I'M NOT TRYING TO BE MEAN,

31:02.071 --> 31:03.152
BUT I THINK THAT YOU SHOULD
HEAR IT FROM ME.

31:03.152 --> 31:04.283
OKAY.

31:04.283 --> 31:06.615
JACKSON AND APRIL
ARE STILL TOGETHER.

31:08.447 --> 31:09.698
WHAT?

31:09.698 --> 31:12.581
WEBBER JUST WALKED IN ON ALEX,
ME, AND THEM IN A CLOSET.

31:12.581 --> 31:14.163
I-I'M CONFUSED.

31:14.163 --> 31:16.625
YOU KNOW, I-I KNOW THAT YOU WERE
TRYING TO PUNISH THEM

31:16.625 --> 31:18.877
WHEN YOU MADE YOUR COMPLAINT,
BUT THEY'RE FINE, STEPH.

31:18.877 --> 31:19.959
THEY'RE GREAT.

31:19.959 --> 31:23.552
THE ONLY ONE
WHO'S BEING PUNISHED IS ME!

31:23.552 --> 31:25.554
THIS IS GONNA FORCE
ALEX AND ME APART!

31:25.554 --> 31:26.765
DIDN'T YOU GUYS
JUST BREAK UP?

31:26.765 --> 31:28.177
NO, WE FAKED IT.

31:28.177 --> 31:29.468
I'M SO CONFUSED.

31:29.468 --> 31:30.769
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU DO

31:30.769 --> 31:32.601
WHEN YOUR LITTLE HEART
GETS BROKEN, STEPH?

31:32.601 --> 31:34.183
YOU TALK ABOUT IT
WITH YOUR FRIENDS.

31:34.183 --> 31:36.565
YOU DON'T FILE
A COMPLAINT!

31:36.565 --> 31:39.478
I DON'T KNOW HOW MANY TIMES
I HAVE TO TELL YOU THIS.

31:39.478 --> 31:40.609
IT WAS AN ANON--

31:40.609 --> 31:43.322
AN ANONYMOUS COMPLAINT,
WHICH YOU FILE

31:43.322 --> 31:46.115
BECAUSE YOU'RE AFRAID
IF PEOPLE FIND OUT IT WAS YOU,

31:46.115 --> 31:47.786
THEY'D TREAT YOU LIKE CRAP

31:47.786 --> 31:50.409
INSTEAD OF UNDERSTANDING
OR EVEN TRYING TO UNDERSTAND

31:50.409 --> 31:52.621
THAT IT WASN'T
SOME FRIVOLOUS THING YOU DID

31:52.621 --> 31:54.623
BECAUSE YOUR LITTLE HEART
GOT BROKEN,

31:54.623 --> 31:57.036
BUT A DECISION YOU MADE
BECAUSE YOU FELT

31:57.036 --> 32:00.669
LIKE YOUR MEDICAL EDUCATION
HAD BEEN COMPROMISED.

32:00.669 --> 32:02.301
GOD, I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHY I BOTHERED.

32:02.301 --> 32:04.133
I SHOULD HAVE JUST SIGNED
MY NAME.

32:04.133 --> 32:05.634
[ Chuckling ]
OH!

32:05.634 --> 32:08.887
♪ FOR ONCE IN MY LIFE ♪

32:10.389 --> 32:13.762
♪ GONNA FEEL REAL GOOD ♪

32:13.762 --> 32:15.814
♪ GONNA MAKE A DIFFERENCE ♪

32:15.814 --> 32:18.147
♪ GONNA MAKE IT RIGHT ♪

32:18.147 --> 32:22.521
THIS JOB
IS A PRIVILEGE AND A GIFT,

32:22.521 --> 32:25.274
AND WE ARE SQUANDERING IT.

32:25.274 --> 32:27.987
I ALMOST LOST MY PLACE
IN THIS PROGRAM

32:27.987 --> 32:32.241
BECAUSE I GOT DISTRACTED...
WITH DR. YANG.

32:32.241 --> 32:34.703
AND YOU ARE ALL
LETTING DISTRACTIONS

32:34.703 --> 32:37.246
GET IN THE WAY OF OUR WORK.

32:39.168 --> 32:43.882
WE HAVE A CHANCE HERE
TO ACTUALLY SAVE THIS GIRL.

32:45.544 --> 32:47.926
AND I HAVE AN IDEA.

32:48.757 --> 32:50.089
LOOK.

32:52.221 --> 32:53.472
YOU SLEPT WITH YANG?

32:53.472 --> 32:56.305
♪ AND A ONE MAN'S SOUL ♪

32:56.305 --> 32:57.686
THE ANATOMY'S ALL MESSED UP.

32:57.686 --> 32:59.648
THE TUMOR'S STUCK
TO EVERYTHING IN HERE.

32:59.648 --> 33:00.649
OKAY.

33:00.649 --> 33:02.861
LET'S TRY CLAMPING
THE AORTA.

33:02.861 --> 33:05.024
THAT MAY TEMPORARILY HELP
CURB THE BLEEDING.

33:07.156 --> 33:10.409
NOW I JUST HAVE TO FIND IT.

33:10.409 --> 33:12.661
THIS PATIENT SURVIVED
SIX TYPES OF CANCERS.

33:12.661 --> 33:13.822
THEY WERE ONTO SOMETHING.

33:13.822 --> 33:16.455
YEAH, BUT THEN HE DIED
FROM A SURGICAL COMPLICATION.

33:16.455 --> 33:18.617
SO, IF WE COMBINED
RADIOFREQUENCY ABLATION

33:18.617 --> 33:20.829
WITH AN ANTERIOR-APPROACH
EN BLOC RESECTION...

33:20.829 --> 33:22.381
YES.
YES.
YES.

33:22.381 --> 33:24.002
[ MONITORS BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

33:24.002 --> 33:26.085
V-FIB.
STARTING CARDIAC MASSAGE.

33:26.085 --> 33:28.677
CHARGE THE PADDLES TO 10.

33:28.677 --> 33:31.090
[ ELECTRICITY HUMMING ]

33:31.090 --> 33:32.181
NO, NO, NO, NO.

33:32.181 --> 33:33.682
LOOK. LOOK. LOOK.
LOOK. LOOK. LOOK.

33:33.682 --> 33:35.594
THIS GIVES US
GOOD LOCAL CONTROL.

33:35.594 --> 33:36.765
SO WE CAN TREAT THE TUMOR

33:36.765 --> 33:37.726
WITHOUT COMPROMISING
THE HEALTHY LUNG TISSUE.

33:37.726 --> 33:38.847
EXACTLY.

33:38.847 --> 33:40.519
OKAY, CHARGE TO 20.

33:40.519 --> 33:42.481
CLEAR.
[ ELECTRICITY ZAPS ]

33:42.481 --> 33:45.484
♪ I'VE BEEN A VICTIM
OF A SELFISH KIND OF... ♪

33:45.484 --> 33:46.645
ALL RIGHT.
WE GOT A RHYTHM.
[ SIGHS ]

33:46.645 --> 33:48.777
IT'S WEAK, BUT IT'LL DO.

33:48.777 --> 33:50.649
OKAY, LET'S GET IN THERE
AND FIND THE SOURCE.

33:50.649 --> 33:52.321
Leah: AND WE CAN GET A BIOPSY
WHILE WE'RE IN THERE

33:52.321 --> 33:54.073
TO CUSTOMIZE THE CHEMO
TO HER SPECIFIC TUMOR.

33:54.073 --> 33:55.574
THIS WILL WORK, GUYS.

33:55.574 --> 33:56.785
YEAH.

33:56.785 --> 33:58.036
LET'S GO TELL WEBBER.

33:58.036 --> 34:00.159
♪ COULD IT BE REALLY ME ♪

34:00.159 --> 34:05.084
♪ PRETENDING
THAT THEY'RE NOT ALONE ♪

34:05.084 --> 34:07.926
♪ A WIDOW DEEPLY SCARRED ♪

34:07.926 --> 34:10.169
WE GOT IT!
WE FIGURED IT OUT!

34:10.169 --> 34:11.760
YOU START
WITH RADIOFREQUENCY ABLATION.

34:11.760 --> 34:13.592
Stephanie: THEN YOU TAKE
THE REMAINDER OUT EN BLOC.

34:13.592 --> 34:15.434
AND THE HEALTHY TISSUE
REMAINS HEALTHY.

34:15.434 --> 34:16.595
GUYS --
BUT HERE'S A TWIST --

34:16.595 --> 34:17.596
YOU CAN DO A BIOPSY.

34:17.596 --> 34:18.807
WHICH WILL CUSTOMIZE
HER CHEMO.

34:18.807 --> 34:20.229
THAT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

34:20.229 --> 34:21.310
IT MIGHT HAVE.

34:21.310 --> 34:22.811
IT'S A WORTHY PITCH,

34:22.811 --> 34:25.394
BUT RORY BLED OUT
INTO HER CHEST TONIGHT.

34:25.394 --> 34:28.107
IT LOOKS LIKE IT TORE
INTO HER AORTA.

34:28.107 --> 34:29.648
WE DID EVERYTHING WE COULD.

34:29.648 --> 34:31.150
SHE DIED?

34:32.191 --> 34:33.282
SHE DIED.

34:33.282 --> 34:35.404
♪ ...MIRROR ♪

34:35.404 --> 34:40.659
♪ I'M ASKING HIM
TO CHANGE HIS WAYS ♪

34:40.659 --> 34:46.044
♪ AND NO MESSAGE
COULD HAVE BEEN ANY CLEARER ♪

34:46.044 --> 34:48.917
♪ IF YOU WANT TO MAKE THE WORLD
A BETTER PLACE ♪

34:48.917 --> 34:54.133
♪ TAKE A LOOK AT YOURSELF
AND MAKE THAT CHANGE ♪

34:59.768 --> 35:00.719
WE TRIED EVERYTHING.

35:00.719 --> 35:02.181
Brian:
[ Crying ] NO.

35:02.181 --> 35:03.812
OH, MY GOD.

35:03.812 --> 35:06.024
WE'RE SO SORRY.

35:06.024 --> 35:07.686
[ Crying ] OH! OH!

35:11.530 --> 35:12.821
DO I HAVE IT?

35:14.693 --> 35:16.325
THE GENE --
I WANT TO KNOW IF I HAVE IT.

35:16.325 --> 35:17.696
NO, HONEY.
NOW IS NOT THE TIME.

35:17.696 --> 35:19.077
NO, NOW IS THE TIME,
MOM.

35:19.077 --> 35:21.410
I WANT TO KNOW.

35:21.410 --> 35:23.792
YOU KNOW.

35:23.792 --> 35:24.743
DR. BAILEY TOLD YOU.

35:24.743 --> 35:25.744
ARIEL.

35:25.744 --> 35:27.796
DO I HAVE IT?

35:30.339 --> 35:31.460
YEAH.

35:31.460 --> 35:33.462
[ GASPS ]

35:33.462 --> 35:35.464
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

35:35.464 --> 35:37.636
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY, MOM.

35:37.636 --> 35:39.848
I ALWAYS WANTED TO BE LIKE HER,
AND NOW I AM.

35:39.848 --> 35:41.850
[ Crying ]
I'M JUST LIKE RORY.

35:41.850 --> 35:43.852
[ SIGHS ]

35:46.064 --> 35:48.026
[ CRYING ]

35:50.769 --> 35:52.771
Shh.

35:55.324 --> 35:57.576
REALLY?
WEBBER TOLD ON US?
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

35:57.576 --> 35:59.618
NONE OF US WANT TO BE HERE,
KAREV.

35:59.618 --> 36:00.869
THEN WHY ARE WE?

36:00.869 --> 36:02.040
YOU'RE HAVING A RELATIONSHIP
WITH A SUBORDINATE,

36:02.040 --> 36:03.202
AND THAT IS AGAINST POLICY.

36:03.202 --> 36:04.743
CAN WE NOT TALK
ABOUT MY PERSONAL LIFE?

36:04.743 --> 36:06.375
I'D LOVE
TO NOT TALK ABOUT IT, ALEX,

36:06.375 --> 36:07.916
BUT YOU ARE MAKING ME.

36:07.916 --> 36:09.878
NOW, I REALIZE THAT
WE CANNOT LEGISLATE
FOR ROMANTIC FEELINGS.

36:09.878 --> 36:12.841
OKAY, OBVIOUSLY, WHAT YOU DO
AT HOME IS YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

36:12.841 --> 36:14.843
Callie: LOOK,
WE'RE JUST ASKING THAT, AT WORK,

36:14.843 --> 36:15.844
THINGS REMAIN
STRICTLY PROFESSIONAL.

36:15.844 --> 36:17.506
OH, THAT'S CRAP!
ALEX.

36:17.506 --> 36:18.847
OH, IT'S OKAY
FOR YOU ALL TO FLAUNT

36:18.847 --> 36:20.849
YOUR RELATIONSHIPS
AND YOUR RINGS

36:20.849 --> 36:22.431
AND YOUR -- YOUR --
YOUR HAPPY, LITTLE LIVES

36:22.431 --> 36:23.932
JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE MARRIED?

36:23.932 --> 36:25.063
KAREV, JUST SIT DOWN.
NO!

36:25.063 --> 36:26.305
I'M NOT GONNA LET
A BUNCH OF HYPOCRITES

36:26.305 --> 36:28.477
TELL ME TO KEEP MY PANTS ON
AT WORK

36:28.477 --> 36:29.728
WHEN THIS PLACE WAS BUILT
ON ALL OF YOU

36:29.728 --> 36:31.980
FEELING EACH OTHER UP
IN OUR ON-CALL ROOM!

36:31.980 --> 36:35.193
I'M DONE!
PUNISH ME! WHATEVER!

36:36.865 --> 36:38.817
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

36:42.581 --> 36:46.325
OKAY, SO, THIS IS NOT HOW
WE WANTED TO TELL YOU GUYS THIS,

36:46.325 --> 36:47.626
UM, BECAUSE
IT COULD LOOK LIKE

36:47.626 --> 36:48.787
WE'RE TRYING
TO GET OFF THE HOOK,

36:48.787 --> 36:50.539
WHICH WE ARE NOT.

36:50.539 --> 36:52.421
BUT WE --
WE ARE MARRIED.

36:52.421 --> 36:53.752
WHAT?

36:53.752 --> 36:55.794
YES,
APRIL IS MY WIFE.

36:55.794 --> 36:58.887
SO, OUR SUPPLY-CLOSET ACTIVITY
BREAKS NO RULES.

36:58.887 --> 37:00.138
SINCE WHEN?

37:00.138 --> 37:01.680
SINCE THE WEDDING.

37:01.680 --> 37:04.102
MY OTHER WEDDING.

37:04.102 --> 37:05.304
KEPNER, YOU CONTINUE
TO SURPRISE ME.

37:05.304 --> 37:06.345
[ LAUGHS ]
MM-HMM.

37:06.345 --> 37:08.807
UM, CON-- CONGRATULATIONS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:08.807 --> 37:10.769
THANK YOU.

37:10.769 --> 37:11.770
OKAY.

37:11.770 --> 37:13.522
SO, I SH--
I SHOULD PROBABLY GO.

37:13.522 --> 37:15.904
I'M SO SORRY.
GOOD LUCK.

37:22.781 --> 37:25.033
FILING THAT COMPLAINT
REALLY TOOK BALLS,

37:25.033 --> 37:26.325
BALLS I DIDN'T HAVE.

37:26.325 --> 37:28.957
JO'S GONNA BE SO PISSED AT ME,
ISN'T SHE?

37:28.957 --> 37:30.168
OH, YEAH, SHE IS.

37:30.168 --> 37:32.000
HIDE AT THE BAR?

37:32.000 --> 37:34.132
YES, PLEASE.
ALL RIGHT.

37:34.132 --> 37:36.835
SHANE, WE'RE DRINKING.
YOU'RE COMING.

37:38.046 --> 37:40.719
YOU CAN TRY TO HIDE
FROM A BULLY.

37:40.719 --> 37:43.011
BUT HIDING
WON'T WORK FOR LONG.

37:43.011 --> 37:45.143
YOU'RE GONNA SEND HER FLOWERS,
YOU'RE GONNA APOLOGIZE,

37:45.143 --> 37:48.016
AND THEN YOU ARE
NEVER GOING TO SEE HER AGAIN.

37:48.016 --> 37:50.018
OH,
I'LL TAKE THIS OUTSIDE.

37:50.018 --> 37:50.939
OKAY.

37:50.939 --> 37:52.891
OH, UH, TELL HIM
HE KISSES LIKE A TURTLE'S BUTT.

37:52.891 --> 37:54.272
IS SHE BREAKING UP
WITH HIM FOR YOU?

37:54.272 --> 37:56.445
I CAN'T BE TRUSTED
TO DO IT. I'M CRAZY.

37:56.445 --> 37:58.857
BUT THE FIRST STEP IS ADMITTING
YOU HAVE A PROBLEM, RIGHT?

37:58.857 --> 37:59.818
[ SIGHS ]

37:59.818 --> 38:02.451
NO MORE SECRET ROMANCES,
NO MORE MARRIED MEN.

38:02.451 --> 38:03.992
HEY.

38:05.243 --> 38:06.745
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
THIS WEEKEND?

38:06.745 --> 38:08.246
YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL.
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:08.246 --> 38:10.078
AND YOU'VE ALREADY
SEEN ME NAKED.

38:10.078 --> 38:13.462
SO, YOU MIGHT AS WELL
BUY ME DINNER.

38:16.965 --> 38:21.880
WELL, I ACTUALLY ALREADY
HAVE PLANS WITH MY WIFE, SO...

38:21.880 --> 38:24.973
STUCK IN A TRASH CHUTE --
CHECK.

38:24.973 --> 38:26.885
PRAWN STUCK IN MY LEG --
CHECK.

38:26.885 --> 38:29.888
EMBARRASS MYSELF IN FRONT
OF MY SURGEONS -- DOUBLE CHECK.

38:29.888 --> 38:32.931
YEAH. THAT ABOUT SOUNDS RIGHT.
I CAN DIE NOW.

38:35.934 --> 38:38.276
YOU KNOW,
HE REALLY SHOULD WEAR A RING.

38:38.276 --> 38:39.317
IT'S NOT FAIR,

38:39.317 --> 38:41.199
GOING AROUND LOOKING LIKE THAT
WITHOUT ONE.

38:41.199 --> 38:43.992
TOTALLY AGREE.

38:45.784 --> 38:48.036
THERE'S REALLY
ONLY ONE WAY TO WIN.

38:48.036 --> 38:49.538
IT'S AN INTERESTING IDEA.

38:49.538 --> 38:50.659
MM-HMM.

38:50.659 --> 38:52.951
I WISH WE'D HAD A CHANCE
TO GIVE IT A TRY.

38:52.951 --> 38:54.663
YOU KNOW, BUT MAYBE
WE'LL BE AHEAD OF THE GAME

38:54.663 --> 38:55.664
FOR HER SISTER.

38:55.664 --> 38:56.875
IT WAS --
IT WAS A TEAM EFFORT.

38:56.875 --> 38:58.046
I DON'T WANT TO GET AHEAD
OF MYSELF,

38:58.046 --> 38:59.047
BUT I THINK I'M STARTING

38:59.047 --> 39:00.298
TO MAKE SOME HEADWAY
WITH THOSE KIDS.

39:00.298 --> 39:01.420
OH.

39:01.420 --> 39:02.761
WARREN!

39:02.761 --> 39:04.172
DR. BAILEY,
WE'RE GONNA GO TO JOE'S.

39:04.172 --> 39:05.263
YOU MIND?
CAN BEN COME?

39:05.263 --> 39:07.265
♪ ...WHERE YOU ARE NOW ♪

39:07.265 --> 39:09.057
GO ON.

39:09.057 --> 39:10.599
GO PLAY
WITH YOUR FRIENDS.

39:13.181 --> 39:17.816
♪ DON'T, DON'T YOU WANT ME? ♪

39:17.816 --> 39:19.568
BUT DON'T STAY OUT
TOO LATE.

39:19.568 --> 39:21.440
♪ YOU KNOW I CAN'T BELIEVE IT ♪

39:21.440 --> 39:23.982
♪ WHEN YOU SAY
THAT YOU WON'T SEE ME ♪

39:23.982 --> 39:25.444
[ CATCALLING, WHISTLING ]

39:25.444 --> 39:28.116
♪ DON'T, DON'T YOU WANT ME? ♪

39:28.116 --> 39:29.748
SURE YOU WANT TO COME?
MMM.

39:29.748 --> 39:30.989
JUST RUB THAT
IN OUR FACES.

39:30.989 --> 39:32.290
Ben: I'M GONNA COME OUT.
I'M GONNA COME OUT.

39:32.290 --> 39:33.452
BELIEVE ME --
I'M GONNA GET HOME TONIGHT.

39:33.452 --> 39:35.454
♪ WHEN I HEAR
THAT YOU DON'T NEED ME ♪

39:35.454 --> 39:37.045
YOU HAVE TO FIGHT BACK.

39:37.045 --> 39:38.877
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

39:38.877 --> 39:42.050
THIS MORNING, WE WERE MAKING
PLANS TO SEE HOUSES TOGETHER,

39:42.050 --> 39:44.883
AND NOW
YOU WANT TO BREAK UP.

39:44.883 --> 39:46.635
I THOUGHT I KNEW
WHAT I WANTED.

39:46.635 --> 39:48.887
WHAT, THE HOUSE,
THE KIDS, OR ME?

39:48.887 --> 39:49.928
EMMA, I AM SO SORRY.

39:49.928 --> 39:50.929
DON'T.

39:50.929 --> 39:53.101
I DON'T NEED AN APOLOGY.

39:53.101 --> 39:55.013
I WANT AN EXPLANATION

39:55.013 --> 39:57.225
BECAUSE THE LAST TIME I CHECKED,
WHICH WAS THIS MORNING,

39:57.225 --> 40:00.569
WE WERE ON THE EXACT SAME PAGE,
AND NOW WE'RE NOT.

40:00.569 --> 40:01.570
WHAT CHANGED?

40:01.570 --> 40:05.073
♪ DON'T YOU WANT ME, BABY? ♪

40:05.073 --> 40:06.695
I WANT TO COME HOME
TO SOMEONE AT NIGHT

40:06.695 --> 40:10.739
WHO IS EQUALLY AS PASSIONATE
ABOUT THEIR WORK --

40:10.739 --> 40:12.290
I AM.

40:12.290 --> 40:14.332
EMMA, YOU --

40:14.332 --> 40:19.998
YOU WOULD GIVE UP SURGERY
IN EXCHANGE FOR FAMILY.

40:21.500 --> 40:22.501
[ Voice breaking ]
THAT'S A PROBLEM?

40:22.501 --> 40:26.044
NO. NO, IT'S AMAZING --
FOR YOU.

40:26.044 --> 40:28.096
I WANT YOU TO HAVE THAT --

40:28.096 --> 40:30.549
HOUSE WITH THE BEDROOMS
AND THE KIDS.

40:30.549 --> 40:34.853
IT IS A BEAUTIFUL FUTURE.

40:34.853 --> 40:37.185
BUT I WANT TO COME HOME
AT NIGHT

40:37.185 --> 40:41.189
AND EXCHANGE O.R. STORIES.

40:41.189 --> 40:43.191
[ SIGHS ]

40:43.191 --> 40:44.823
WE WANT DIFFERENT THINGS.

40:44.823 --> 40:48.116
♪ DON'T, DON'T YOU WANT ME? ♪

40:48.116 --> 40:49.237
SO IT'S ME.

40:49.237 --> 40:52.070
EMMA, COME ON.

40:52.070 --> 40:53.331
PLEASE.
JUST PLEASE LET ME GO.

40:53.331 --> 40:54.493
EMMA, EMMA --

40:54.493 --> 40:55.574
I'M GONNA CALL A CAB.

40:55.574 --> 40:59.167
WILL YOU WAIT
A FEW MINUTES

40:59.167 --> 41:01.039
SO THAT I'M GONE
BEFORE YOU LEAVE?

41:01.039 --> 41:02.841
♪ YOU KNOW I CAN'T BELIEVE IT ♪

41:02.841 --> 41:06.424
♪ WHEN I HEAR
THAT YOU DON'T NEED ME ♪

41:06.424 --> 41:08.176
♪ IT'S MUCH TOO LATE TO FIND ♪

41:08.176 --> 41:09.638
♪ WHEN YOU THINK... ♪

41:09.638 --> 41:11.970
AND IF YOU'RE LUCKY ENOUGH
TO GET OUT ALIVE...

41:11.970 --> 41:14.643
♪ YOU BETTER CHANGE IT BACK ♪

41:14.643 --> 41:16.765
♪ OR WE WILL BOTH BE SORRY ♪

41:16.765 --> 41:19.267
...TAKE JUST A MOMENT
TO CELEBRATE...

41:19.267 --> 41:21.059
THE WHITE HOUSE CALLED.

41:21.059 --> 41:22.440
YOU GOT IT?

41:22.440 --> 41:24.102
NO, IT'S MUCH BIGGER
THAN THAT.

41:24.102 --> 41:26.194
THAT'S WHY THE INTERVIEW PROCESS
WAS SO EXHAUSTIVE.

41:26.194 --> 41:29.988
THEY WANT ME
ON THE ADVISORY BOARD.

41:29.988 --> 41:31.369
THEY WANT ME
TO RUN THE THING.

41:32.661 --> 41:34.072
YOU'RE MAD.

41:34.072 --> 41:36.454
NO.

41:36.454 --> 41:37.706
I'M NOT MAD.

41:37.706 --> 41:40.669
I-I JUST -- I'M -- I'M --
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU.

41:40.669 --> 41:41.790
BUT THERE ISN'T ROOM

41:41.790 --> 41:44.122
FOR ME TO TAKE MY CAREER
TO THE NEXT LEVEL

41:44.122 --> 41:45.754
AND FOR YOU
TO RUN THE THING.

41:45.754 --> 41:47.716
DEREK, THAT'S FRUSTRATING.

41:47.716 --> 41:49.297
MM-HMM.

41:49.297 --> 41:52.050
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:52.050 --> 41:53.722
COME HERE.

41:53.722 --> 41:55.053
